fields.name: SWEET POTATO PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup flour (120 g) 3/4 cup mashed sweet potatoes (180 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 2 eggs 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pan-cake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE BANANA PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 banana, mashed (100 g) 1 cup almond milk (120 ml) 2/3 cup whole wheat pastry flour (80 g) 2 tablespoons baking cocoa (10 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: RED VELVET PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1/3 cup oat flour (30 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 egg 3 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (45 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon coconut flour (10 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 5 drops red food coloring

Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: S’MORES PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: BATTER 3/4 cup oats (60 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 egg 2 egg whites 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons baking cocoa (10 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt TOPPINGS 1 1/2 low-fat graham crackers, crushed (25 g)  2 tablespoons marshmallow cream (15 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter. 4.  Top pancakes with graham cracker crumbs, marshmallow cream, and chocolate chips.

fields.name: BUTTERMILK PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup flour (120 g) 1/2 cup low-fat buttermilk (120 ml) 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (55 g) 1 egg 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tea - spoon baking soda 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt

Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.ingredients: 1 cup pancake mix (120 g) 3/4 cup water (180 ml) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 2 cream-filled cookies, crumbled (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: VANILLA CINNAMON PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup oat flour (80 g) 1 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (230 g) 1 cup egg whites (240 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE-CHIP PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup oat flour (80 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 3 egg whites 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate chips (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER BANANA PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup oat flour (60 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 3 egg whites 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon peanut butter (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 banana, sliced (50 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter. 4. Top pancakes with banana slices

fields.name: PUMPKIN SPICE PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 2/3 cup oat flour (55 g) 1/4 cup pumpkin (60 g) 1 egg white 2 tablespoons low-fat cottage cheese (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pumpkin pie seasoning 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: NO WHEY, NO PROBLEM PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 6-ounce container fat-free Greek yogurt (170 g) 1/2 cup oat flour (40 g) 1 egg 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into the skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter.

fields.name: BANANA PROTEIN OATCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 banana, mashed (100 g) 1 cup oats (80 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (165 g) 1 egg 1 egg white 1/2 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (15 g)  1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Use hands to shape some batter into an oatcake and place in pan. After a few minutes, flip oatcake to cook other side. Repeat the process for the remaining batter.

fields.name: CINNAMON ROLL MUG CAKES
fields.ingredients: CAKE 1/4 cup flour (30 g) 1 egg 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons unsweetened applesauce (15 g) 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt GLAZE 1 tablespoon light butter (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon ICING 2 tablespoons light cream cheese (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon almond milk (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a small bowl, mix together cake ingredients. 2.  Spray inside of coffee mug with nonstick- cooking spray and fill with batter. Microwave for 1 minute. Stir and microwave in 30-second interval until cooked. 3.  Remove cake from mug and cut in half. 4.  In separate bowl, combine glaze ingredients and microwave for 15 seconds or until melted. Drizzle glaze on top of cakes. 5.  In a small bowl, combine ingredients for icing and mix with fork. Top glazed cakes with icing.

fields.name: CLASSIC PROTEIN FRENCH TOAST
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup egg substitute (120 ml) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 4 slices bread 1 banana, sliced (100 g) 1/4 cup sugar-free syrup (60 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a shaker bottle, combine egg substitute, almond milk, protein powder, sweetener, and cinnamon. Shake until batter reaches a smooth consistency. Pour into bowl. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Dip a slice of bread into batter and coat. Place slice in skillet or griddle and cook for a few minutes on each side. Repeat process with remaining bread. 4. Top French toast with banana slices and syrup.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER FRENCH TOAST
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup egg whites (120 ml) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g)  1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 3 slices bread 2 tablespoons peanut butter (30 g) 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (35 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a shaker bottle, combine egg whites, almond milk, protein powder, and sweetener. Shake until batter reaches a smooth consistency. Pour into bowl. 2.  Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 3.  Dip a slice of bread into batter and coat. Place slice on pan and cook for a few minutes on each side. Repeat process with remaining bread. 4.  Spread peanut butter on tops of French toast slices, drizzle with chocolate syrup, and top with chocolate chips.

fields.name: FLUFFY PROTEIN WAFFLES
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup flour (90 g) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (60 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1 egg 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons coconut flour (15 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray heated waffle maker with nonstick cooking spray. 3.  Pour half the batter into waffle maker. Cook for 3–5 minutes, checking periodically to make sure waffles aren’t burning. Repeat process with remaining batter.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN WAFFLES
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 cup low-fat cottage cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup egg whites (120 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g) 2 tablespoons light whipped cream (5 g) 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (35 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine oats, cottage cheese, egg whites, protein powder, sweetener, baking powder, vanilla extract, and salt. Blend until smooth. 2.  Spray heated waffle maker with nonstick cooking spray. 3.  Pour half the batter into waffle maker. Cook for 3–5 minutes, checking periodically to make sure waffles aren’t burning. Repeat process with remaining batter. 4.  Top waffles with chocolate chips, whipped cream, and chocolate syrup.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE HAZELNUT PROTEIN CRÊPES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup egg whites (240 ml) 1/2 cup low-fat cottage cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup oat flour (40 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate hazelnut spread (40 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine egg whites, cottage cheese, oat flour, protein powder, and sweetener. Blend until smooth. 2.  Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 3.  Pour thin layer of batter into pan and let cook for approximately 1 minute. Repeat with remaining batter to make four crêpes in all. 4.  Place crêpes on plate and spread with chocolate hazelnut spread. Roll up each crêpe.

fields.name: APPLE CINNAMON PROTEIN CRÊPES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup egg whites (240 ml) 1/4 cup low-fat cottage cheese (60 g) 1/2 cup oat flour (40 g) 1/2 cup applesauce (30 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. 2.  Spray a stove top pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 3.  Pour thin layer of batter into pan and let cook for approximately 1 minute. Repeat with remaining batter to make four crêpes in all. 4. Place on plate and roll up each crêpe.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN CRÊPES
fields.ingredients: 1 egg 3/4 cup egg whites (180 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g)  1 tablespoon peanut butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon powdered peanut butter (5 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (35 g) 2 tablespoons light whipped cream (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine the egg, egg whites, protein powder, melted peanut butter, powdered peanut butter, and sweetener. Blend until smooth. 2.  Spray a stove top pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 3.  Pour thin layer of batter into pan and let cook for approximately 1 minute. Repeat with remaining batter to make three crêpes in all. 4.  Place on plate and roll up each crêpe. Top with chocolate syrup and whipped cream.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PROTEIN BREAKFAST CAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 cup egg whites (120 ml) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (35 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate syrup. Microwave for 45 seconds and stir. 2.  Remove from microwave and stir again, especially around edges. If necessary, continue to microwave in 30-second intervals until fully cooked. 3. Top cake with chocolate syrup.

fields.name: BAKED MINT CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1 cup oats (80 g) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon cocoa powder (5 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 tablespoon chocolate chips (10 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon peppermint extract 3 drops green food coloring
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients to bowl and stir. 3.  Cover top of bowl with aluminum foil. Bake for 20–25 minutes.

fields.name: S’MORES PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 packet diet hot chocolate mix (10 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 low-fat graham cracker sheet (15 g) 1/3 cup mini marshmallows (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats, almond milk, and hot chocolate mix and stir. Microwave for 2 minutes. 2.  Add chocolate chips and protein powder and stir. 3.  Top with crushed graham cracker and marshmallows.

fields.name: CHEESECAKE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup oats (60 g) 1 tablespoon cream cheese (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free gelatin cheesecake mix (10 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 2 cream-filled cookies (20 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free whipped cream (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350oF (177°C). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray and add oats. 3.  In separate bowl, combine cream cheese and vanilla extract. Microwave for 10–15 seconds or until softened. 4.  Add cream cheese mixture to bowl with oats. Add protein powder, cheesecake mix, sweetener, baking powder, salt, and almond milk and stir. Bake for 15 minutes. 5.  Remove from oven and let cool on counter for 10 minutes. 6.  Top with crumbled cookies and whipped cream.

fields.name: PEANUT-BUTTER-CUP PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (30 g) 1 tablespoon peanut butter (15 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g) 1 tablespoon baking cocoa (10 g) 1 tablespoon powdered peanut butter (5 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free whipped cream (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2. Add remaining ingredients to bowl and stir.

fields.name: BANANA-SPLIT PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup water (240 ml) 1 (6oz.) container strawberry Greek yogurt (170 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (15 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate chips (30 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 banana, sliced (100 g) 2 tablespoons light whipped cream (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and water. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2.  Add yogurt, protein powder, chocolate chips, and vanilla extract to bowl and stir. 3. Top with banana and whipped cream.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE BROWNIE OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 banana, mashed (50 g) 1/2 cup low-fat chocolate milk (120 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon caramel extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients to bowl and stir. 3.  Cover top of bowl with aluminum foil. Bake for 20–25 minutes.

fields.name: OVERNIGHT CINNAMON BANANA PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 banana, sliced (50 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (165 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1. In a bowl, combine all ingredients and stir. 2.  Cover top of bowl with aluminum foil. Refrigerate overnight or for at least 4 hours.

fields.name: OVERNIGHT CHOCOLATE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 3 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (20 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g) 1 tablespoon baking cocoa (5 g) 1 banana, sliced (100 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except banana and stir. 2.  Cover top of bowl with aluminum foil. Refrigerate overnight or for at least 4 hours. 3. Serve topped with bananas.

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED STEEL-CUT OATS
fields.ingredients: 8 cups water (2 L) 2 cups steel-cut oats (320 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 2 bananas, sliced (200 g) 2 teaspoons cinnamon 1 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients and stir. 2. Cook for 6 hours on low.

fields.name: CINNAMON ROLL PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free cream cheese (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2. Add remaining ingredients to bowl and stir.

fields.name: LEMON BLUEBERRY PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1/2 cup blueberries (75 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (30 g) 1 tablespoon lemon juice (15 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 teaspoons walnuts, crushed (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2. Add remaining ingredients to bowl and stir.

fields.name: PUMPKIN PIE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup pumpkin puree (120 g) 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 2 teaspoons molasses (15 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon 1/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine pumpkin, oats, and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2. Add remaining ingredients to bowl and stir.

fields.name: PEACHES AND CREAM PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1/2 cup peaches, sliced (85 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons light cream (30 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 low-fat graham cracker sheet (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2.  Add all remaining ingredients except for graham cracker to bowl and stir. 3.  Crush graham cracker and sprinkle on top of oats.

fields.name: APPLE PIE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1 cup water (240 ml) 1/2 cup apples, chopped (65 g) 1/4 cup applesauce (65 g) 2 tablespoons light syrup (30 ml) 2 tablespoons almonds (20 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray pot with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients except oats and protein powder and place over medium heat. Let cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. 2. Add oats to bowl. Add protein powder and stir.

fields.name: KEY LIME PIE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons lime juice (30 ml) 1 tablespoon honey (20 g) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 low-fat graham cracker sheet (15 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2.  Add all remaining ingredients except for graham cracker to bowl and stir. 3.  Crush graham cracker and sprinkle on top of oats.

fields.name: BAKED BANANA-WALNUT PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1 banana, mashed (100 g) 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 egg white 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (30 g) 2 tablespoons walnuts, crushed (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients and stir. 3.  Cover top of bowl with aluminum foil. Bake for 20–25 minutes.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER & JELLY PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons sugar-free jelly (30 g) 1 tablespoon peanut butter, softened (15 g) 1 tablespoon powdered peanut butter (5 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2. Add remaining ingredients to bowl and stir.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY SHORTCAKE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1/4 cup strawberries, mashed (40 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (30 g) 1 tablespoon coconut flakes (10 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 low-fat graham cracker sheet (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine oats and almond milk. Microwave for 2 minutes and stir. 2.  Add all remaining ingredients except for graham cracker to bowl and stir. 3.  Crush graham cracker and sprinkle on top of oats.

fields.name: SPRINKLED PROTEIN DONUTS
fields.ingredients: DOUGH 1 banana, mashed (100 g) 2 egg whites 1 cup oat flour (80 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt ICING 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (65 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons colored sprinkles (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine dough ingredients and stir until batter forms. 3.  Spray donut tray with nonstick cooking spray and pour batter into six donut holes. Bake for 6–8 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In another bowl, combine Greek yogurt, protein powder, and sweetener and stir. 5.  Dip each donut into icing to coat one side. Remove and top with sprinkles.

fields.name: DOUBLE CHOCOLATE PROTEIN DONUTS
fields.ingredients: DOUGH 3/4 cup canned pumpkin (180 g) 3/4 cup flour (90 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 egg 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 3 tablespoons cocoa powder (15 g) 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (30 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt ICING 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (65 g) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate sprinkles (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine dough ingredients and stir until batter forms. 3.  Spray donut tray with nonstick cooking spray and pour batter into six donut holes. Bake for 6–8 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In another bowl, combine Greek yogurt, protein powder, and sweetener and stir. 5.  Dip each donut into icing to coat one side. Remove and top with sprinkles.

fields.name: SPINACH AND EGG BREAKFAST BURRITO
fields.ingredients: 4 whole wheat tortillas 4 cups spinach (120 g) 1 cup sliced mushrooms (95 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 3 eggs 4 egg whites 1/4 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon oregano 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 3/4 cup reduced-fat feta cheese (85 g) 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes (60 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Microwave tortillas for 1 minute. 2.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on stove top pan and place over medium heat. 3.  Add spinach, mushrooms, and onion to pan and cook for 2 minutes or until soft. Add eggs, egg whites, and seasonings to pan and cook until eggs are done. 4.  Remove from stove and distribute egg mixture among tortillas. Top with feta and sun-dried tomatoes and wrap tortillas.

fields.name: PESTO BREAKFAST PIZZA
fields.ingredients: 2 pitas 1/4 cup basil pesto sauce (60 g) 1 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (110 g) 1 cup spinach (30 g) 2 eggs 1/4 cup diced onion (40 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Line baking sheet with parchment paper. 2.  Place pitas on prepared baking sheet and spread basil pesto sauce on top of each. Top with mozzarella. 3.  Place spinach around edges of pitas, leaving room in the middle. 4.  Crack an egg and add to center of one pita. Repeat with other egg and pita. Top with onion and season with salt and pepper. 5. Bake for 10 minutes. Top with Parmesan.

fields.name: TURKEY BACON BREAKFAST SKILLET
fields.ingredients: 4 slices turkey bacon (30 g) 2 potatoes, diced (300 g) 1/4 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon Southwestern seasoning 2 eggs, beaten 4 egg whites 1/2 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (55 g) 1 teaspoon hot sauce (optional)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a skillet, cook bacon over medium heat. Once fully cooked, remove from pan and set aside. 2.  In the same skillet, combine potatoes and seasonings. While potatoes are cooking, add eggs and egg whites. Cook until eggs are done and potatoes are soft. 3. Crush cooked bacon into pieces. 4.  Remove potatoes and eggs from skillet and divide between two bowls. Top with cheddar and bacon. Add hot sauce, if desired.

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED BREAKFAST CASSEROLE
fields.ingredients: 6 cups hash browns (960 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1/2 cup chopped red bell pepper (80 g) 1/2 cup chopped green bell pepper (80 g) 12 ounces ground turkey, cooked (450 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon oregano 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 4 cups fat-free cheddar cheese (440 g) 6 eggs, beaten 1 1/2 cups egg whites (355 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Line bottom of slow-cooker with 3 cups of hash browns and top with 1/4 cup onion, 1/4 cup red bell pepper, 1/4 cup green bell pepper, 6 ounces ground turkey, seasonings, and 2 cups cheddar. Repeat pattern with remaining ingredients to create a layered breakfast casserole. 3.  In a bowl, mix eggs and egg whites. Pour into slow-cooker. 4. Cook for 4 hours on high or 6–8 hours on low.

fields.name: BREAKFAST STUFFED PEPPERS
fields.ingredients: 4 red bell peppers, halved, seeds removed (500 g) 2 eggs 6 egg whites 6 slices bacon, cooked and chopped (25 g) 1/2 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (55 g) 1/2 cup spinach (15 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking pan lined with aluminum foil. Place bell pepper halves on top. 3.  In a bowl, combine eggs, egg whites, bacon, mozzarella, spinach, onion, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Mix well. 4.  Pour egg mixture evenly into bell pepper halves. Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes. 5.  Remove aluminum foil and top peppers with cheddar. Cook uncovered for additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

fields.name: CHICKEN AND EGG-WHITE BREAKFAST MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 2 cups egg whites (480 ml) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 2 teaspoons chipotle seasoning 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 8 ounces chicken breast, cooked and shredded (225 g) 1/4 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine egg whites, almond milk, and seasonings. Stir and set aside. 3.  Spray a muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. Place chicken at the bottom of each muffin hole. Top with cheddar. 4.  Pour egg-white mixture evenly into each muffin hole. Bake for 30 minutes.

fields.name: HASH-BROWN BREAKFAST MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 3 cups hash browns (480 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 3/4 cup egg substitute (180 ml) 3 eggs 1 1/2 cups fat-free cheddar cheese (165 g) 1/4 cup chopped red bell pepper (45 g) 1/4 cup chopped green onion (25 g) 4 slices bacon, cooked and chopped (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Spray a muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. Distribute hash browns evenly into muffin holes. Season with garlic powder, crushed red pepper, and salt. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown. 3.  Add egg substitute, eggs, cheddar, bell pepper, green onion, and bacon to bowl and mix. Distribute egg mixture evenly into each muffin hole. Bake for additional 15 minutes.

fields.name: BACON AND EGG BREAKFAST MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 12 slices bacon, cooked (50 g) 10 eggs 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1/2 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (55 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Spray a muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. Line each muffin hole with a slice of bacon. 3.  In a bowl, combine eggs, almond milk, and seasonings and stir. Pour egg mixture into muffin holes. Top with onion and half the cheddar. Bake for 20 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheddar. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

fields.name: SAUSAGE AND PANCAKE BREAKFAST MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 2 cups pancake mix (240 g) 2 eggs 2/3 cup almond milk (160 ml) 1/2 cup light syrup (120 ml) 4 precooked turkey sausage patties, diced (225 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). Spray a muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, combine pancake mix, eggs, almond milk, and syrup. 3.  Fill each muffin hole 2/3 of the way with pancake mixture. Evenly distribute turkey sausage patties among muffin holes. Bake for 15 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and top with extra syrup if desired.

fields.name: SOUTHWESTERN BREAKFAST BOWL
fields.ingredients: 1 cup egg whites (240 ml) 1 egg 1/4 cup black beans (65 g) 1/4 cup corn (40 g) 2 tablespoons chopped onion (30 g) 1 cup spinach (30 g) 2 tablespoons salsa (30 g) 1 teaspoon Southwestern seasoning 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/4 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place on stove over medium heat. 2.  Pour egg whites, egg, black beans, corn, and onion into pan. 3.  When eggs have cooked, add spinach, salsa, and seasonings. 4.  Serve egg and beans in a bowl, topped with cheddar.

fields.name: EGG AND OATS SCRAMBLE
fields.ingredients: 1/3 cup oats (25 g) 1/2 cup egg whites (120 ml) 1 egg 1 cup spinach (30 g) 1/3 cup tomatoes, diced (80 g) 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 2 tablespoons salsa (30 g) 1/4 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, stir together oats, egg whites, and egg. Let eggs soak in the oats for a few minutes. 2.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place on stove over medium heat. 3.  Pour oat mixture on pan. Add spinach, tomatoes, seasonings, and salsa. Cook for 5 minutes or until eggs are done. Top with cheddar.

fields.name: BACON AVOCADO BREAKFAST BAGEL
fields.ingredients: 2 eggs, beaten 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 2 bagels, halved and toasted 2 tablespoons fat-free mozzarella cheese (15 g) 2 slices bacon, cooked (g) 1/2 avocado, pitted (85 g) 1 tablespoon lime juice (15 ml) 2 tomato slices (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.  Add eggs, almond milk, and seasonings, and begin to cook eggs. 3.  Once eggs are fully cooked, transfer to top of two bagel halves. Sprinkle mozzarella over eggs. Break bacon apart with hands and set on top of mozzarella. 4.  Scrape out insides of avocado into bowl, mash using a fork, and mix in lime juice. Spoon avocado mixture on top of bacon and top with tomato slices. 5.  Set other half on each bagel to make sandwiches. Cut each sandwich in half and serve.

fields.name: BAKED HARD-BOILED EGGS
fields.ingredients: 12 eggs 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 325°F (165°C). 2.  Place eggs in holes of a muffin pan to prevent them from moving. Bake for 30 minutes. 3.  Remove from oven and place eggs in ice water for 10 minutes. Peel shell from eggs and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

fields.name: BACON, CHEESE, AND RANCH DEVILED EGGS
fields.ingredients: 12 hard-boiled eggs, shells removed 5 slices bacon, cooked and chopped (20 g) 1/2 cup light ranch dressing (120 g) 1/4 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (60 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolk. Put yolks in a bowl and mash. 2.  Add bacon, ranch dressing, cheddar, and seasonings to bowl. Mix all ingredients together. 3.  Spoon egg-yolk mixture into the holes left by yolk in eggs.

fields.name: BAKED BIRTHDAY CAKE PROTEIN OATS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oat flour (60 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 tablespoon coconut flour (10 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (55 g) 2 tablespoons applesauce (30 g) 1 egg 1/2 teaspoon cake batter extract 1 tablespoon sprinkles   FROSTING 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (120 g) 1 teaspoon zero calorie sweetener 1 tablespoon vanilla sugar-free pudding mix (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until smooth. 3.  Spray 7 ounce ramekin with nonstick cooking spray. 4.  Pour mixture into ramekin. Bake for 10-12 minutes.  Let cool on counter for 5 minutes. 5.  In another bowl, combine all frosting ingredients and mix until smooth.  Top oats with frosting.

fields.name: BAKED S’MORES PROTEIN OATS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oat flour (60 g) 1/2 scoop whey protein powder (15 g) 1/2 scoop casein protein powder (15 g) 1 tablespoon mini chocolate chips (15 g) 1 tablespoon marshmallow bits (3 g) 1 tablespoons sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1/3 cup Greek yogurt (75 g) 2 tablespoons applesauce (30 g) Toppings: 1/4 cup mini marshmallows (10 g) 1/2 sheet crushed graham cracker (10 g) 1 teaspoon mini chocolate chips (3 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 375°F (190°F). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray. Add all ingredients to bowl and stir. 3.  Bake for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and top with marshmallows, crushed graham cracker, chocolate chips and bake for additional 5 minutes. 4. Broil on high for 1 minute if desired.

fields.name: FRUITY CEREAL PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup pancake mix (110 g) 1 scoop fruity cereal whey (30 g) 1 scoop vanilla casein (30 g) 3 tablespoons sweetener (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 2 eggs 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) Topping 1/2 cup fruity cereal (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour some batter into a skillet or griddle. After a few minutes, flip pancake to cook other side. Repeat the process with the remaining batter. 4. Top pancakes with fruity cereal.

fields.name: BAKED COOKIE DOUGH PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oat flour (60 g) 1/2 scoop whey protein powder (15 g) 1/2 scoop casein (15 g) 3 tablespoons coconut flour (20 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 egg 2 tablespoons applesauce (30 g) 1/4 cup Greek yogurt (55 g) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2. In a bowl, combine all ingredients. 3.  Lightly spray ramekin with nonstick cooking spray and bake for 10 minutes.

fields.name: DOUBLE CHOCOLATE PROTEIN DONUTS
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup pancake mix 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 cup canned pumpkin (240 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 egg 1 tablespoon melted butter (15 g)   ICING 2 tablespoons melted chocolate chips (30 g) 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 scoop whey protein powder (15 g) 1 teaspoon chocolate sugar-free pudding mix (3 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener  1 tsp baking cocoa 2 tbsp colored sprinkles (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine dough ingredients and stir until batter forms. 3.  Spray donut tray with nonstick cooking spray and pour batter into nine donut holes. Bake for 15 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In another bowl, combine melted chocolate, Greek yogurt, protein powder, sweetener, and baking cocoa and stir. 5. Dip each donut into icing to coat one side.

fields.name: AIR FRIED PROTEIN FRENCH TOAST STICKS
fields.ingredients: 4 slices of bread, cut into thirds 1 egg 1/2 cup egg whites (120 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon  Pinch of powdered sweetener
fields.recipe: 1. Arrange bread slices into baking dish. 2.  Whisk together egg, egg whites, milk, whey protein, sweetener, and cinnamon. 3. Pour egg mixture over bread. 4.  Place bread in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 5.  Cook at 375°F (190°F) for 10 minutes, flipping halfway. 6.  Remove from air fryer and dust with powdered sugar if desired.

fields.name: CRUNCHY HANDHELD BREAKFAST WRAP
fields.ingredients: 2 eggs 2 egg whites 1/4  teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper  1-1/3 cup shredded potatoes (170 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 2 slices turkey bacon, cooked 1/4 cup fat-free shredded cheddar cheese 2 flour tortillas
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on stove top pan over medium heat. Add eggs, salt, pepper, and cook until eggs are done. 2.  Season potatoes with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Place potatoes in a single layer in air fryer basket and cook at 350°F (177°C) for 15 minutes. 3. Lay 2 tortillas on a flat surface. 4.  Divide up egg mixture and potatoes amongst the 2 tortillas, placing in the middle. 5.  Place 1 bacon slice and 2 tablespoons of cheese on top. 6.  Fold edges of tortilla inwards to form a pentagon. 7.  Spray a skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. Cook tortilla for 1 minute on each side.

fields.name: COOKIES AND CREAM PROTEIN PANCAKES
fields.ingredients: PANCAKES 1 cup pancake mix (110 g) 1 scoop casein protein (30 g) 1 scoop whey protein (30 g) 3 tablespoons unsweetened baking cocoa (15 g) 3 tablespoons sweetener (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 2 eggs  1/2 cup Greek yogurt (120 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml)   FILLING 1/2 cup Greek yogurt 1 tablespoon white chocolate sugar free pudding       mix (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine pancake mix, casein protein, whey protein, baking cocoa, sweetener, baking powder. Slowly stir in eggs, yogurt, and almond milk. 2.  Spray a skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. 3.  Pour 1/4 of batter onto skillet and cook pancake for 2 minutes each side. 4.  In a bowl, combine greek yogurt and pudding mix. Spread filling in between pancakes and stack.

fields.name: BAKED BROWNIE PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 egg 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1/2 banana (55 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 tablespoon baking cocoa (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  Spray oven-safe bowl or ramekin with nonstick cooking spray. 3.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. 4. Pour batter into prepared ramekin. 5. Bake for 15 minutes.

fields.name: FRUITY CEREAL PROTEIN DONUTS
fields.ingredients: DOUGH 3/4 cup whole wheat flour (90 g) 2 scoops protein powder (60 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 cup canned pumpkin (240 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 egg 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/4 cup fruity cereal (10 g)   ICING 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (120 g) 1 scoop protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)   TOPPING 1/2 cup fruity cereal (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine dough ingredients and stir until batter forms. 3.  Spray donut tray with nonstick cooking spray and pour batter into six donut holes. Bake for 15 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In another bowl, combine Greek yogurt, protein powder, and sweetener and stir. 5.  Dip each donut into icing to coat one side. Remove and top with fruity cereal.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN WAFFLES
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup flour (90 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons coconut flour (30 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup Greek yogurt (60 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 egg 2 tablespoons chocolate chips (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Spray heated waffle maker with nonstick cooking spray. 3.  Pour half the batter into waffle maker. Cook for 3-5 minutes or until golden brown. 4. Repeat process with remaining batter.

fields.name: OVERNIGHT PEANUT BUTTER CUP PROTEIN OATMEAL
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon peanut butter (15 g) 2 teaspoons baking cocoa (10 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 2 teaspoons powdered peanut butter (5 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients. 2.  Add oatmeal mixture to a mason jar, cover, and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

fields.name: BACON-WRAPPED STUFFED JALAPEÑO CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces chicken breasts, flattened (455 g) 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 8 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (225 g) 1 jalapeño, diced (25 g) 1 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (85 g) 8 slices bacon (60 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking pan covered with aluminum foil. Place chicken breasts on pan and add seasonings. 3.  In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, jalapeño, and cheddar. 4.  Spoon out cream cheese mixture into each chicken breast. Roll up chicken breasts around mixture and wrap with 2 slices of bacon each. Skewer with toothpick to hold together. 5.  Bake for 45 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: HONEY MUSTARD PRETZEL CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 4 ounces pretzels, crushed (115 g) 1/3 cup panko breadcrumbs (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 3/4 cup honey mustard (180 g) 16 ounces chicken breast (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  In a bowl, combine pretzels, panko breadcrumbs, and seasonings, and mix with hands. Put honey mustard in a separate bowl. 3.  Dip chicken in honey mustard and then in pretzel breading to coat. Place on prepared baking pan. Sprinkle any remaining pretzel and breadcrumb mixture over chicken breasts. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: BAKED HONEY BALSAMIC CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup honey (225 g) 1/2 cup balsamic vinegar (180 ml) 3 tablespoons soy sauce (45 ml) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 16 ounces chicken breast (450 g) 2 tablespoons sesame seeds (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, stir together honey, balsamic vinegar, soy sauce, olive oil, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 2.  Poke holes in chicken breasts using fork and add to bag with marinade. Let marinate for at least 2 hours in refrigerator. 3.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking pan covered with aluminum foil. 4.  Place chicken on baking sheet. Pour excess marinade from bag onto chicken. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). 5. Sprinkle sesame seeds over top of chicken.

fields.name: CHICKEN AND POTATO CASSEROLE
fields.ingredients: 5 potatoes, cubed (1,000 g) 20 ounces chicken breast, chopped (570 g) 3 tablespoons olive oil (45 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon oregano 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 2 cups fat-free cheddar cheese (240 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on a baking pan covered with aluminum foil. Add potatoes and chicken to pan and mix. 3.  Drizzle olive oil over potatoes and chicken and add seasonings. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). 4.  Remove from oven and top with onion and cheddar. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

fields.name: GRILLED KEY WEST CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup soy sauce (180 ml) 3 tablespoons lime juice (45 ml) 2 tablespoons honey (40 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 16 ounces chicken breasts (450 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, stir together soy sauce, lime juice, honey, olive oil, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 2.  Poke holes in chicken breasts using fork and add to bag with marinade. Let marinate for at least 2 hours in refrigerator. 3.  After marinating, add chicken to grill over medium heat. Grill 5 minutes on each side or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: CHEESY CHICKEN BAKE
fields.ingredients: 4 chicken breasts (910 g) 1 (15-ounce) can corn, drained (425 g) 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained (425 g) 1 (10-ounce) can diced tomatoes and green chilies,         drained (285 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 4 tablespoons lime juice (60 ml) 10 ounces melty queso cheese, cubed (285 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (125°C). 2.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking pan covered with aluminum foil and place chicken on top. 3.  Add corn, black beans, diced tomatoes, onion, seasonings and lime juice to chicken and cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). 4.  Remove from oven and top with queso cheese. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED CHICKEN AND SWEET POTATOES
fields.ingredients: 12 ounces chicken breasts (340 g) 1 cup chopped onion (160 g) 1 cup chopped carrot (115 g) 1 sweet potato (185 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1 cup water (240 ml) 1 tablespoon soy sauce (15 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Place all ingredients into slow-cooker. Cook for 4 hours on high or 6–8 hours on low.

fields.name: GRILLED CHICKEN KABOBS
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces chicken breasts, cubed (680 g) 1 onion, sliced (200 g) 1 red bell pepper, sliced (200 g) 1 green bell pepper, sliced (200 g) 1 cup sliced mushrooms (110 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Slide chicken, onion, red bell pepper, green bell pepper, and mushrooms onto skewers in repeating pattern. Season with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. 2.  Set kabobs onto grill over medium heat and grill for about 7 minutes, then flip kabobs to grill other side until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: LETTUCE CHICKEN WRAPS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground chicken (455 g) 1 (8-ounce) can water chestnuts, drained and diced        (225 g) 1/4 cup hoisin sauce (65 g) 1/4 cup chopped green onion (25 g) 3 tablespoons soy sauce (45 ml) 1 tablespoon garlic, minced (15 g) 1 tablespoon sesame seeds (10 g) 2 teaspoons ground ginger 8 romaine lettuce leaves (115 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray and place on stove over medium heat. Add chicken and cook for 10 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). 2.  Add water chestnuts, hoisin sauce, green onion, soy sauce, garlic, sesame seeds, and ground ginger. Continue to cook for 5 minutes. 3.  Remove from stove and scoop chicken mixture into lettuce leaves.

fields.name: CRISPY BAKED CHICKEN NUGGETS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/4 cup panko breadcrumbs (15 g) 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese (10 g) 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 2 egg whites 14 ounces chicken breast, cubed (400 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking sheet covered with aluminum foil. 2.  In a bowl, combine breadcrumbs, panko breadcrumbs, Parmesan, and seasonings, and mix with hands. Put egg whites in another bowl. 3.  Dip chicken in egg whites and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven, flip chicken, and bake for additional 5 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED FIESTA CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces chicken breast (680 g) 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained (425 g) 1 (15-ounce) can corn, drained (425 g) 8 ounces fat-free cream cheese (225 g) 1 1/2 cups salsa (230 g) 1/2 cup water (120 ml) 1 teaspoon ground cumin 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon chili powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Place all ingredients in slow-cooker. Break apart cream cheese with fork and mix all ingredients. Cook 4 hours on high or 6–8 hours on low.

fields.name: CRISPY COCONUT CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 1/3 cup unsweetened coconut flakes (45 g) 1/4 cup flour (30 g) 2 tablespoons coconut flour (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 2 eggs 1 pound chicken breast tenderloins (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Spray nonstick cooking spray on baking pan covered with aluminum foil. 2.  In a bowl, combine coconut flakes, flour, coconut flour, and seasonings. In a separate bowl, beat the eggs. 3.  Dip chicken in eggs and then into coconut mixture to coat. Place on prepared baking pan. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: BUFFALO CHICKEN WINGS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup flour (60 g) 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon chili powder 12 chicken wings (225 g) 2 tablespoons light butter (30 g) 1/2 cup buffalo style hot sauce (120 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, mix flour and seasonings. 2.  Set chicken wings on a plate. Sprinkle flour mixture over wings, coating each completely. Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate for 45–60 minutes. 3.  Preheat oven to 400°F (204°C). Cover baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 4.  Place wings on prepared baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes. Remove from oven, flip, and bake for additional 15 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). Transfer cooked wings to a mixing bowl. 5.  In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and then add hot sauce and garlic salt, stirring frequently. Once butter is fully melted, pour over bowl of chicken wings and stir to coat.

fields.name: BUFFALO CHICKEN POPPERS
fields.ingredients: 2 (12.5-ounce) cans chicken, drained (710 g) 1/2 cup breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/2 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (55 g) 1/4 cup buffalo-style hot sauce (60 ml) 2 eggs 2 tablespoons light ranch dressing (30 g) 2 tablespoons chopped green onion (10 g) 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon chili powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  In a bowl, mix together all ingredients. Form mixture into seven balls and place on prepared baking pan. 3.  Lightly spray top of chicken balls with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes.

fields.name: BUFFALO POPCORN CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 2 eggs 3/4 cup buffalo hot sauce (180 ml), divided 1 cup panko breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/2 cup cornmeal (70 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon chili powder 16 ounces chicken breast tenderloins, cubed (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C). Cover a baking sheet with aluminum foil. 2.  In a bowl, stir together eggs and 1/4 cup of the hot sauce. In a separate bowl, combine panko breadcrumbs, cornmeal, and seasonings by mixing with hands. 3.  Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in breadcrumb mixture to fully coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). 5.  Transfer chicken to mixing bowl and add remaining hot sauce. Stir to coat.

fields.name: GRILLED BUFFALO CHICKEN BURGERS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground chicken (455 g) 1/2 cup buffalo hot sauce (120 g) 1/4 cup breadcrumbs (30 g) 2 tablespoons light ranch dressing (30 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon oregano
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands. Shape into four burgers and place onto grill. 2.  Grill for 5 minutes and flip burgers. Grill for additional 5 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: CRISPY CHICKEN SANDWICH
fields.ingredients: 2 cups corn flake cereal, crushed (60 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 1 tablespoon lemon juice (15 ml) 24 ounces chicken breasts, flattened (680 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C). Cover bottom of a baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a small bowl, combine cereal, salt, and pepper. Spread onto flat plate. 3.  In a separate bowl, stir together almond milk and lemon juice. 4.  Dip chicken breasts in almond milk and then in cereal to coat. Place in prepared baking pan. 5.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). Remove foil and cook for additional 5 minutes.

fields.name: CRISPY POPCORN CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 2 tablespoons sweet and sour sauce (60 g) 2 egg whites 2 cups panko breadcrumbs (120 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon pepper 20 ounces chicken breast, cubed (570 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). Cover bottom of a baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, stir together sweet and sour sauce and egg whites. In a separate bowl, combine panko breadcrumbs and seasonings. 3.  Dip chicken in egg white mixture and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place in prepared baking pan. 4.  Bake chicken for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and flip chicken to cook other side. Bake for additional 10 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: CRISPY CHICKEN FINGERS
fields.ingredients: 2 eggs 1 egg white 1 cup almond flour (110 g) 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 teaspoon chili powder 20 ounces chicken tenderloins (565 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (204°C). Line a baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a small bowl, stir together eggs and egg white. In a separate bowl, mix almond flour and seasonings. 3.  Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in almond flour to coat. Place in prepared baking pan. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray for crispiness. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: BAKED BARBEQUE CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup lemon juice (120 ml) 3 tablespoons olive oil (45ml) 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 24 ounces chicken breasts (680 g) 1 cup barbeque sauce (240 ml), divided
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (225°C). 2.  In a bowl, stir together lemon juice, olive oil, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 3.  Poke holes in chicken breasts using fork and add to bag with marinade. Seal and set flat on a plate. Refrigerate for at least one hour. 4.  Cover bottom of a baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Set chicken on pan. Bake for 30 minutes. 5.  Remove from oven and pour 1/2 cup of the barbeque sauce over chicken. Return to oven for 10 minutes. 6.  Remove from oven and pour remaining barbeque sauce over chicken. Bake for additional 10 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: GRILLED SWEET HONEY CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1/3 cup soy sauce (160 ml) 1/4 cup honey (85 g) 1/4 cup Dijon mustard (60 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon paprika 16 ounces chicken breast tenderloins (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, stir together all ingredients except chicken. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 2.  Poke holes in chicken using a fork and add to bag with marinade. Seal and set flat on a plate. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. 3.  Set chicken on grill over medium to high heat and grill for about 10 minutes. Flip to grill other side. Grill until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: BAKED SRIRACHA CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 2 pounds chicken breasts, sliced (910 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/3 cup honey (115 g) 1/4 cup sriracha sauce (60 ml) 2 tablespoons low sodium soy sauce (30 ml) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 tablespoon lime juice (15 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (225°C). Cover bottom of a pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Place chicken on pan and add seasonings. 3.  In a bowl, stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken. 4.  Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: BAKED LEMON BASIL CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 1 cup lemon juice (240 ml) 2 tablespoons olive oil (30 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon basil 1 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 24 ounces chicken breasts (680 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 425°F (225°C). 2.  In a bowl, stir together lemon juice, olive oil, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 3.  Poke holes in chicken using a fork and add to bag with marinade. Seal and set flat on a plate. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. 4.  Cover bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil, with enough to fold over the top of pan. Place chicken in pan. Season chicken. Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: OVEN-FRIED CHICKEN BREASTS
fields.ingredients: 1 cup corn flakes, crushed (100 g) 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese (10 g) 1 teaspoon pepper 1 teaspoon cayenne pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 2 egg whites 12 ounces chicken breasts (340 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Cover bottom of a baking pan with aluminum foil. 2. I n a bowl, combine corn flakes, Parmesan, and seasonings. Put egg whites in another bowl. 3.  Dip chicken in egg whites and then in cornflake mixture to coat. Place in prepared pan. 4.  Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 50 minutes. Remove foil top and lightly spray nonstick cooking spray on chicken. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: CHICKEN TERIYAKI STIR-FRY
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup water (120 ml) 4 cups broccoli (340 g) 12 ounces chicken breast, cooked (340 g) 2 cups brown rice, cooked (320 g) 1/4 cup teriyaki sauce (60 ml) 2 tablespoons chopped green onion (10 g) 2 tablespoons soy sauce (30 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.  Add water, broccoli, and chicken to pan. Cook for 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender. 3.  Add remaining ingredients. Continue to cook for 5 minutes.

fields.name: CRISPY ORANGE CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup cornstarch (95 g) 1/3 cup egg whites (80 ml) 3/4 cup panko breadcrumbs (45 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1 pound chicken breast tenderloins, cubed (455 g) 3 tablespoons orange sauce (30 g) 1 tablespoon sesame seeds (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Add cornstarch to small bowl and egg whites to another bowl. In a third bowl, combine breadcrumbs and seasonings and mix with hands. 3.  Dip chicken in cornstarch, then in egg whites, and then in breadcrumbs to coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Lightly spray top of chicken with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 30 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). 5.  Transfer chicken to a mixing bowl. Add orange sauce and sesame seeds. Stir to coat.

fields.name: CHICKEN FRIED RICE
fields.ingredients: 4 ounces chicken, cooked and sliced (115 g) 1 cup broccoli (85 g) 1 egg 1/2 cup peas (70 g) 1/2 cup sliced mushrooms (50 g) 1/4 cup chopped carrot (30 g) 2 tablespoons soy sauce (30 ml) 1 cup rice (160 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.  Add all ingredients except rice to pan. Continue to cook until vegetables are tender and egg is fully cooked. 3. Add rice and continue to cook for 5 minutes.

fields.name: SWEET AND SOUR CHICKEN STIR-FRY
fields.ingredients: 1 pound chicken breasts, sliced (455 g) 2 tablespoons soy sauce (30 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1 bag frozen stir-fry vegetables (455 g) 1 cup brown rice, cooked (110 g dry) 1/2 cup sweet and sour sauce (140 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.   Add chicken, soy sauce, and seasonings. Cook chicken to internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). 3.  Add vegetables and rice. Continue to cook until vegetables are thawed. 4.  Transfer stir-fry to bowl and stir in sweet and sour sauce.

fields.name: BEEF AND CHEESE NACHOS
fields.ingredients: 4 ounces lean ground beef (115 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1/4 cup chopped green bell pepper (45 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 cup fat-free refried beans (125 g) 1/2 cup salsa (120 g) 2 tablespoons taco sauce (30 g) 2 ounces oven-baked tortilla chips (55 g) 3/4 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (85 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.   Add beef, onion, bell pepper, and seasonings. Break beef into pieces with spatula. Cook for 10 minutes or until beef reaches internal temperature of 160°F (71°C). 3.  In separate pot over low heat, combine refried beans, salsa, and taco sauce. Continuously stir and cook until warm. Add to pan with beef and stir. 4.  Put chips on a plate and top with beef and bean mixture. Sprinkle cheddar on top.

fields.name: GRILLED CHICKEN QUESADILLA
fields.ingredients: 3 ounces chicken breast, cooked and sliced (85 g) 1 teaspoon taco seasoning 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 2 tortillas 1/2 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (55 g) 2 tablespoons chopped onion (20 g) 2 tablespoons chopped red bell pepper (20 g) 2 teaspoons lime juice (10 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.   Add chicken and seasonings and warm for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and set aside. 3.  Place a tortilla in the pan. Top with chicken and distribute evenly. Sprinkle with cheddar. Top with onion, pepper, and lime juice. Place second tortillas on top of chicken. 4.  Cook quesadilla for 3 minutes per side. Cut in quarters and serve.

fields.name: CREAMY CHICKEN ENCHILADAS
fields.ingredients: 8 ounces low-fat cream cheese (230 g) 1 cup salsa (250 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 1 (15-ounce) can black beans (425 g) 8 ounces chicken breasts, cooked and sliced (230 g)  6 tortillas 1 1/2 cups fat-free cheddar cheese (170 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). Cover bottom of a baking pan with aluminum foil. 2.  Spray a pot with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 3.  Add cream cheese, salsa, and seasonings. Break apart cream cheese with a spatula and continue to cook. 4.  Add beans and chicken to pot and stir. 5.  Divide chicken mixture between tortillas, wrap tightly, and set in prepared pan. Sprinkle with cheddar and cover top of pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 30 minutes.

fields.name: OVEN-BAKED CHICKEN PARMESAN
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup panko breadcrumbs (45 g) 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (20 g) 2 teaspoons basil 2 teaspoons garlic powder 1 teaspoon oregano 2 egg whites 32 ounces chicken breasts, halved (900 g) 1 cup marinara sauce (250 g) 3/4 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (90 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). Cover bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan, and seasonings and mix with hands. Put egg whites in another bowl. 3.  Dip chicken in egg whites and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place in prepared pan. 4.  Cover top of baking pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 40 minutes. Remove foil top and pour marinara sauce over chicken. Sprinkle mozzarella on top of sauce. Bake for 5 additional minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: CHICKEN PESTO PASTA
fields.ingredients: 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 2 teaspoons garlic, minced (10 g) 10 ounces chicken breasts, sliced (285 g) 1 (16-ounce) box bowtie pasta (455 g) 1/2 cup basil pesto sauce (120 g) 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes (60 g) 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon oregano
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2. Heat olive oil in pan, add garlic, and sauté. 3.  Add chicken and cook until it reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). 4.  In a separate pot, cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain and transfer to large bowl. 5.  Add chicken and remaining ingredients to bowl and mix.

fields.name: FETTUCCINE CHICKEN ALFREDO
fields.ingredients: 2 tablespoons light butter (30 g) 1 teaspoon lemon zest 1 tablespoon flour (10 g) 1 cup almond milk (240ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 4 ounces fat-free cream cheese (115 g) 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese (65 g) 2 teaspoons parsley 2 teaspoons garlic powder 12 ounces fettuccine (340 g) 12 ounces chicken breasts, cooked and sliced (340 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a pan, melt butter on medium heat. Slowly add lemon zest, flour, almond milk, and salt. Continue stirring until thickened. 2.  Add cream cheese, Parmesan, parsley, and garlic powder. Continue stirring until smooth and thick. Leave sauce simmering on low heat. 3.  Cook fettuccine noodles according to instructions on package. Once cooked, drain noodles but save 1 cup hot water. Transfer noodles to mixing bowl. 4.  Pour sauce over pasta and mix to distribute. Pour small amounts of hot water onto noodles until sauce is spread evenly. Top with chicken slices.

fields.name: HONEY DIJON CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup Dijon mustard (180 g) 1/2 cup honey (160 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon basil 1 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon pepper 32 ounces chicken breasts (900 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 425°F (225°C). 2.  In a bowl, stir together mustard, honey, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 3.  Poke holes in chicken using fork and add to bag with marinade. Seal bag and set flat on a plate. Refrigerate for at least one hour. 4.  Cover bottom of a pan with aluminum foil. Add chicken and pour remaining marinade from bag over chicken. Cover top of pan with aluminum foil. 5.  Bake for 50 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C).

fields.name: PULLED BARBECUE CHICKEN SANDWICHES
fields.ingredients: 12 ounces chicken breasts (340 g) 3/4 cup chopped onion (120 g) 2 teaspoons chili powder 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon oregano 2/3 cup barbecue sauce (180 g) 6 whole wheat hamburger buns
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. Add chicken, onion, and seasonings. Cook for 4 hours on high or 6–8 hours on low. 2.  Transfer chicken to a bowl. Pull apart using forks and mix in barbecue sauce. 3.  Toast hamburger buns and fill with chicken to make sandwiches.

fields.name: CHICKEN BURRITO BOWL
fields.ingredients: 3 tablespoons chopped chipotle peppers in adobo                               sauce (50 g) 1/2 cup lime juice (120 ml) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 2 teaspoons taco seasoning 1 teaspoon basil 1/2 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 18 ounces chicken breasts, chopped (510 g) CILANTRO LIME RICE 1 tablespoon olive oil (15ml) 1 cup basmati rice (180 g) 2 cups water (480 ml) 2 tablespoons cilantro, chopped (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, mix together chipotle peppers, lime juice, olive oil, and seasonings. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 2.  Poke holes in chicken using fork and add to bag with marinade. Seal bag and set flat on a plate. Refrigerate for at least one hour. 3.  In a pan over medium heat, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). Once cooked, remove from stove. 4.  Make the cilantro lime rice: In a saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add rice and lime juice and toast for 1 minute. Add water and cook according to package instructions. Add cilantro and stir. 5.  Combine rice and chicken. Add additional ingredients of choice, such as black beans, pico de gallo, corn, cheese, and guacamole.

fields.name: CHIPOTLE CHICKEN SALAD
fields.ingredients: DRESSING 4 tablespoons fat-free sour cream (60 g) 1 tablespoon chopped chipotle pepper in adobo        sauce (15 g) 2 teaspoons lime juice (10 ml) 1 teaspoon cilantro, chopped 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon salt SALAD 4 cups lettuce (200 g) 4 ounces chicken breast, cooked and sliced (110 g)  1/2 avocado, sliced (85 g) 1/4 cup black beans (65 g) 6 tomato slices (60 g) 1/4 cup corn (40 g)
fields.recipe: 1. In a bowl, stir together dressing ingredients. 2.  Place lettuce into container with lid. 3.  Pour dressing onto lettuce and cover; shake to coat lettuce in dressing. Top salad with chicken, avocado, black beans, tomato, and corn.

fields.name: GRILLED CHICKEN CAESAR SALAD
fields.ingredients: DRESSING 1/3 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (75 g) 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (20 g) 1 tablespoon garlic, minced (15 g) 1 tablespoon anchovy paste (15 g) 1 teaspoon lemon juice (5 ml) 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper SALAD 3 cups lettuce (170 g) 4 ounces grilled chicken breast, sliced (115 g)
fields.recipe: 1. In a bowl, mix together dressing ingredients. 2.  In another bowl, top lettuce with grilled chicken. Pour dressing over top.

fields.name: BEEF TACO SALAD WITH CREAMY CILANTRO DRESSING
fields.ingredients: SALAD 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 4 ounces lean ground beef (115 g) 1 teaspoon taco seasoning 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon salt 3 cups lettuce (150 g) 1/2 cup pinto beans, rinsed (110 g) 1/4 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (55 g) DRESSING 1/2 cup fat-free sour cream (120 g) 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped (20 g) 3 tablespoons lime juice (45 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. Add onion and cook for 5 minutes or until soft. 2.  Add beef and seasonings to pan and continue cooking until beef is fully cooked and reaches internal temperature of 160°F (71°C). 3.  In a bowl, top lettuce with beans, and then with beef mixture. 4.  In a separate bowl, stir together dressing ingredients. Pour over salad. 5. Top salad with cheddar.

fields.name: CHOPPED CHICKEN SALAD WITH ALMOND GINGER DRESSING
fields.ingredients: SALAD 3 cups lettuce (150 g) 1/2 cup shredded carrot (65 g) 2 tablespoons chow mein noodles (15 g) 2 tablespoons chopped green onion (10 g) 1 tablespoon sesame seeds (10 g) 1 tablespoon almonds, sliced (10 g) 4 ounces chicken breast, cooked and chopped (115 g) DRESSING 1/4 cup coconut milk (60 ml) 2 tablespoons soy sauce (30 ml) 1 tablespoon almond butter, softened (15 g) 1 teaspoon garlic, minced (5 g) 1 teaspoon ground ginger 1 teaspoon rice wine vinegar (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Combine lettuce, carrot, noodles, onion, sesame seeds, and almonds in a bowl and toss. Top with chicken. 2.  In a separate bowl, stir together dressing ingredients until mixed. Pour over salad.

fields.name: SOUTHWESTERN TURKEY MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground turkey (455 g) 2 egg whites 1/2 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (55 g) 1/4 cup black beans (65 g) 1/4 cup corn (40 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1/4 cup oats (20 g) 2 teaspoons Southwestern seasoning 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce (10 ml) 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands. 3.  Spray muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. Shape turkey mixture into muffins and place into 10 muffin holes. 4.  Bake for 30 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).MICHAEL KORY’S ULTIMATE COOKBOOK

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED GROUND TURKEY CHILI
fields.ingredients: 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 16 ounces ground turkey (455 g) 1 cup chopped onion (160 g) 1/2 cup chopped green bell pepper (90 g) 2  (15-ounce) cans tomato sauce (850 g) 1 (15-ounce) can black beans (425 g) 3 tablespoons chili powder 1 teaspoon ground cumin 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon black pepper
fields.recipe: 1. In a pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. 2.  Add turkey, onion, and bell pepper. Break ground turkey apart with spatula and cook for 10 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). Remove from stove. 3.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. Add turkey mixture and remaining ingredients and mix. Cook for 4 hours on high or 6 hours on low.

fields.name: CLASSIC HOME COOKED MEATLOAF
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces lean ground beef (680 g) 1 egg, beaten 3/4 cup oats (60 g) 1/2 cup sugar-free ketchup (120 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce (15 ml) 1 teaspoon oregano 1 teaspoon parsley 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands. 3.  Spray a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and add meat- loaf mixture. Bake for 50 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 160°F (71°C). 4. Remove from oven and cut into 6 slices.

fields.name: TURKEY CHEESEBURGER MEATLOAF
fields.ingredients: 20 ounces ground turkey (565 g) 3 slices bacon, cooked and chopped (15 g) 1 slice bread, ripped into pieces 1 egg 1 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup sugar-free ketchup (120 g) 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 tablespoon horseradish mustard (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands. 3.  Spray 5 x 9-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and add meatloaf mixture. Bake for 50 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). 4. Remove from oven and cut into 6 slices.

fields.name: GROUND TURKEY STUFFED PEPPERS
fields.ingredients: 1 cup quinoa, dry (185 g) 16 ounces ground turkey (455 g) 1 (14.5-ounce) can diced tomatoes (410 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce (15 ml) 2 teaspoons olive oil (10 ml) 7 red bell peppers, halved, seeds removed 1/2 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (60 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Line a baking pan with aluminum foil. 2.  Cook quinoa according to package instructions. Set aside. 3.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. Add turkey and cook for 10 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). 4.  Add diced tomatoes, onion, seasonings, Worcestershire sauce, and olive oil. Continue to cook for 5 minutes. 5. Add cooked quinoa and stir. 6.  Fill peppers with turkey and quinoa mixture.
