Place filled peppers into prepared baking pan. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 30 minutes. 7.  Remove foil from top, sprinkle stuffed peppers with mozzarella, and place back in oven 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

fields.name: TURKEY JALAPEÑO POPPERS
fields.ingredients: 8 ounces ground turkey, cooked (225 g) 4 ounces low-fat cream cheese, softened (115 g)  1/4 cup chopped onion 1 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (115 g), divided 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 12 jalapeños, halved and seeded (170 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In small bowl, combine cooked turkey, cream cheese, onion, 1/3 cup of the mozzarella, and seasonings. Stir until blended. 3.  Cover baking pan with aluminum foil and place jalapeños on top. Fill each jalapeño with cream cheese mixture. Bake for 20 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven. Sprinkle with remaining 2/3 cup mozzarella and bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

fields.name: TURKEY AND PEPPER JACK MELT
fields.ingredients: 4 slices bread 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 2 slices pepper jack cheese 5 ounces turkey, sliced (140 g) 2 tomato slices (20 g) 2 tablespoons basil, chopped
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.  Brush bread with butter. Add 1 slice pepper jack to bread, then half the turkey, 1 tomato slice, and 1 tablespoon basil. Top with another bread slice to create sandwich. Repeat process with remaining ingredients. 3.  Add sandwiches to pan and cook for 2 minutes each side or until cheese is melted.

fields.name: CHEESEBURGER MACARONI AND CHEESE
fields.ingredients: 20 ounces lean ground beef (565 g) 1 1/2 cups sliced portobello mushrooms (140 g) 1 cup chopped onion (120 g) 1 cup tomato sauce (250 g) 1 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 2 cups elbow pasta (225 g) 2 cups water (470 ml) 2 cups fat-free cheddar cheese (225 g) 1 cup panko breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese (30 g) 1 tablespoon parsley flakes
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. Add ground beef and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). 2.  Add mushrooms and onion. Continue to cook. 3.  Add tomato sauce and seasonings while stirring frequently. 4.  In a pot, combine elbow pasta and water. Boil water, then let simmer for 15 minutes while covered with lid. 5.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Drain excess water from pasta, add cheddar, and stir until melted. Add beef mixture and stir. 6.  Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray and add macaroni mixture. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and mozzarella. Bake for 10 minutes. 7. Top with parsley flakes.

fields.name: CAJUN TURKEY BURGERS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground turkey (455 g) 1/2 cup breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce (15 ml) 1 tablespoon Cajun seasoning 2 teaspoons hot sauce (10 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic, minced (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper 4 hamburger buns
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except hamburger buns and mix with hands. 2.  Shape mixture into 4 burgers and place on grill. Grill for 5 minutes and flip. Grill for additional 5 minutes or until turkey reaches internal temperature of 165°F (74°C). 3.  Add to hamburger buns and garnish with toppings of choice.

fields.name: JALAPEÑO CHEDDAR BURGERS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces lean ground beef (455 g) 1 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1/2 cup chopped jalapeños (70 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper 4 hamburger buns
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except hamburger buns and mix with hands. 2.  Shape mixture into 4 burgers and place onto grill. Grill for 5 minutes and flip. Grill for additional 5 minutes or until beef reaches internal temperature of 160°F (71°C). 3.  Add burgers to hamburger buns and garnish with toppings of choice.

fields.name: BACON STUFFED BURGERS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces lean ground beef (455 g) 4 slices bacon, cooked and chopped (15 g) 3/4 cup low-fat cheddar cheese (85 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 1 teaspoon minced garlic (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 4 hamburger buns
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except hamburger buns and mix with hands. 2.  Shape mixture into 4 burgers and place onto grill. Grill for 5 minutes and flip. Grill for additional 5 minutes or until beef reaches internal temperature of 160°F (71°C). 3.  Add burgers to hamburger buns and garnish with toppings of choice.

fields.name: CRISPY CHICKEN SANDWHICH
fields.ingredients: 20 ounces chicken breasts, flattened and quartered  (570 g) 1/2 cup pickle juice (120 ml) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 cup flour (60 g) 1/2 cup Panko breadcrumbs (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon paprika  1/2 teaspoon celery seeds 1/2 teaspoon pepper  1/2 teaspoon salt 2 eggs 4 hamburger buns
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine chicken, pickle juice, and milk. Pour into sealable plastic bag. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes in refrigerator. 2.  In a bowl, Combine flour, breadcrumbs, sweetener, and seasonings. In a separate bowl, beat the eggs. 3.  Remove chicken from marinade and dredge in egg mixture then flour mixture. 4.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Cook at 350°F (177°C) for 15-20 minutes, flipping halfway. 5.  Assemble sandwich and add lettuce, tomatoes and pickles, if desired.

fields.name: CRISPY PANKO TILAPIA
fields.ingredients: 3/4 cup panko breadcrumbs (45 g) 1 teaspoon lemon zest 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/2 cup coconut milk (120 ml) 16 ounces tilapia, patted dry (455 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 2 tablespoons lemon juice (30 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Cover bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, combine breadcrumbs, lemon zest, and seasonings, and mix with hands. Put coconut milk in another bowl. 3.  Dip tilapia in coconut milk and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place in prepared pan. Cover pan with aluminum foil. Bake for 15 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and pour butter over top of tilapia. Return to oven uncovered for additional 5 minutes or until tilapia reaches internal temperature of 145°F (63o°C). 5. Squeeze lemon juice over tilapia.

fields.name: BROILED PARMESAN TILAPIA
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese (40 g) 2 tablespoons light mayonnaise (30 g) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon lemon juice (15 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon dill 16 ounces tilapia, patted dry (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Turn broiler to high. Cover bottom of baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, mix together Parmesan, mayonnaise, butter, lemon juice, and seasonings. 3.  Set tilapia filet’s on baking pan and broil for 3 minutes. Remove from oven and flip tilapia. Spread Parmesan mixture on top. 4.  Broil for additional 3 minutes. Ensure tilapia reaches internal temperature of 145°F (63°C).

fields.name: TOMATO WALNUT TILAPIA
fields.ingredients: 2 tablespoons lemon juice (30 ml) 16 ounces tilapia, patted dry (455 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1/4 cup walnuts, chopped (30 g) 1/4 cup breadcrumbs (30 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest 8 tomato slices (80 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Turn broiler to high heat. 2.  Spray a pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. Add lemon juice and tilapia. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 3 minutes each side and then remove from stove. 3.  In a bowl, mix walnuts, breadcrumbs, butter, and lemon zest. 4.  Line baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Set tilapia filet’s on baking pan. Top with tomato slices. Spoon walnut mixture over tilapia. 5.  Broil for 3 minutes. Ensure tilapia reaches internal temperature of 145°F (63°C).

fields.name: CRISPY OVEN-BAKED SHRIMP
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder 2 egg whites 1 egg, beaten 3 tablespoons lemon juice (45 ml) 9 ounces shrimp, tails removed (255 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, combine breadcrumbs and seasonings. In another bowl, stir together egg whites, egg, and lemon juice. 3.  Dip shrimp in egg mixture and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Pour melted butter over shrimp. Bake for 20 minutes or until crispy.

fields.name: TUNA PATTIES
fields.ingredients: 3 (5-ounce) cans tuna, drained (425 g) 2 eggs, beaten 1/2 cup breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 2 tablespoons chopped green onion (10 g) 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard (10 g) 1 teaspoon parsley 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except olive oil and mix with hands. Form into 4 patties. 2.  Add olive oil to a pan and place over medium heat. 3.  Add tuna patties and cook for 5 minutes per side.

fields.name: TURKEY PEPPERONI PIZZA BAGELS
fields.ingredients: 2 bagels, sliced 1/2 cup pizza sauce (125 g) 1/2 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (55 g) 2 tablespoons low-fat cheddar cheese (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon oregano 6 slices turkey pepperoni, quartered (10 g) 3 tablespoons basil, chopped (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 420°F (215°C). 2.  Place sliced bagels on a pizza pan rounded- side down. 3.  Spread pizza sauce on bagels. Top with mozzarella, cheddar, garlic powder, oregano, and turkey pepperoni. Bake for 6–8 minutes. 4. Top with each pizza with basil.

fields.name: BARBECUE CHICKEN PIZZAS
fields.ingredients: 2 pitas 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1/4 cup barbeque sauce (70 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon onion powder 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (110 g) 4 ounces chicken breast, cooked and sliced (85 g) 2 tablespoons diced onion (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat over to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Place pitas on a pizza pan and brush with olive oil. 3.  Spread barbeque sauce on top of pitas and top with seasonings, mozzarella, chicken, and onion. Bake for 10 minutes.

fields.name: CHICKEN AND RANCH POCKET PIZZAS
fields.ingredients: 8 ounces chicken breast, cooked and diced (200 g)  1/4 cup chopped onion (40 g) 1 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (110 g) 5 tablespoons light ranch dressing (75 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon oregano 1/4 teaspoon pepper 1 cup spinach (30 g) 3 pitas, halved
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat over to 400°F (205°C). 2.  In a bowl, stir together chicken, onion, mozzarella, ranch dressing, and seasonings. 3. Add spinach leaves and stir again. 4.  Open pitas and add an equal amount of chicken mixture to each one. 5.  Spray nonstick cooking spray on top of each pita and bake for 10 minutes.

fields.name: PERSONAL PITA PIZZAS
fields.ingredients: 2 pitas 2 teaspoons olive oil 1/2 cup pizza sauce (190 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon basil 1/2 teaspoon oregano 3/4 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (85 g) 2 tablespoons low-fat cheddar cheese (15 g) Parmesan cheese
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat over to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Place pitas on a pizza pan and brush with olive oil. 3.  Spread pizza sauce on top of pitas. Top with seasonings, mozzarella, cheddar, and toppings of your choice. Bake for 10 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and sprinkle Parmesan on top.

fields.name: ZUCCHINI PIZZA BOATS
fields.ingredients: 4 zucchini, halved (800 g) 16 ounces ground turkey, cooked (450 g) 1 cup pizza sauce (240 ml) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 cup low-fat mozzarella cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese (40 g) 1 tablespoon crushed red pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat over to 400°F (205°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2.  Scoop out insides of zucchini. Set insides aside, and set zucchini on prepared baking sheet. 3.  In a large bowl, combine turkey, pizza sauce, olive oil, and seasonings. Mix until ingredients are combined. 4.  Scoop turkey mixture and fill 8 zucchini halves. Top with mozzarella, Parmesan, and crushed red pepper. 5.  Bake for 20 minutes or until cheeses are melted.

fields.name: CAULIFLOWER CRUST PIZZA
fields.ingredients: CRUST 2 cups grated cauliflower (500 g) 1/4 cup water (60 ml) 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese (40 g) 1/2 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (55 g) 1 egg 1 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon basil 1/2 teaspoon garlic   TOPPINGS 1/2 cup pizza sauce (120 ml) 3/4 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (85 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 2.  In a pot, steam cauliflower over boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender. Once cooled, place cooked cauliflower on plate and press dry with towel. 3.  Make crust:  In a bowl, stir together cauliflower, Parmesan, mozzarella, egg, and spices. Form into dough with hands and shape into pizza on baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes. 4.  Add toppings:  Remove crust from oven and spread with pizza sauce. Top with mozzarella. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

fields.name: FAST-FOOD STYLE GRILLED NUGGETS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces chicken breast, cubed (455g) 3/4 cup pickle juice (180 ml) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon onion powder 1 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Combine chicken, pickle juice, and milk into sealable plastic bag. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes in refrigerator. 2.  Remove chicken from marinade, add to a bowl, add seasonings, and combine. 3.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with non-stick cooking spray. 4.  Cook at 375°F (190°F) for 10-12 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (77°C).

fields.name: CHICKEN BACON RANCH WRAPS
fields.ingredients: 18 ounces chicken breast (510 g) 1 teaspoon olive oil (5 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper ½ teaspoon garlic powder ½ teaspoon chili powder ½ teaspoon cumin 3 large tortillas 1/4 cup fat-free mozzarella (30 g) 1/4 cup avocado (40 g) 1 cooked bacon strip, crumbled 1 tablespoon green onions, chopped 2 tablespoons fat-free ranch (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine chicken, olive oil, and seasonings. Mix to coat. 2.  Spray pan with non-stick cooking spray. Place chicken on pan over medium heat and cook for 6-8 minutes per side or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (77°C).  Slice into pieces. 3.  Distribute cooked chicken, mozzarella cheese, bacon crumbles, green onions and ranch among tortillas and wrap tightly. 4.  Cook wraps on pan over medium heat for 2 minutes on each side.

fields.name: HOMEMADE PIZZA BAGEL BITES
fields.ingredients: 8 mini bagels (cut in half) 1 cup pizza sauce (250 g) 2 cups low-fat mozzarella (225 g) 16 turkey pepperoni (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon basil
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  Place sliced bagels on a baking sheet, rounded-side down. 3.  Spread pizza sauce on bagels. Top with mozzarella, pepperoni, and basil. 4. Bake for 8-10 minutes.

fields.name: LEMON PEPPER CHICKEN TENDERS
fields.ingredients: 2 eggs 1/2 cup flour (60 g) 1 teaspoon lemon pepper 3/4 cup panko breadcrumbs (45 g) 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese (15 g) 1 tablespoon lemon pepper 1 tablespoon garlic powder 1 tablespoon onion powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 20 ounces chicken breast tenderloins   SAUCE 3 tablespoons butter (45 g) 1 tablespoon honey (20 g) 1 tablespoon chili garlic hot sauce 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder  1/2 teaspoon pepper 2 tablespoons lemon juice (30 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a shallow dish, mix flour and 1 tablespoon lemon pepper seasoning. 2.  In a bowl, combine breadcrumbs, parmesan, and seasonings. In a separate bowl, beat eggs. 3.  Cover chicken tenders in flour mixture. Dip chicken into eggs and then into seasoned breadcrumb mixture to fully coat. 4. Repeat with remaining chicken tenders. 5.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Cook at 375°F (190°C) for 12 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (77°C). 6.  Combine sauce ingredients in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently. Once butter is fully melted, pour sauce over chicken tenders and stir to coat.

fields.name: HONEY GARLIC CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces chicken tenderloins (455 g) 3 tablespoons cornstarch (25 g) 1 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon onion powder 1/2 teaspoon chili powder 1/2 teaspoon salt  1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 tablespoon butter 1/4 cup soy sauce (60 ml) 3 tablespoons honey (60 g) 2 tablespoons minced garlic (30 g) 1 tablespoon rice vinegar (15 ml) 1 tablespoon chili garlic hot sauce (15 ml) 1 teaspoon minced ginger
fields.recipe: 1.  Add chicken to a large mixing bowl with cornstarch, oregano, onion powder, chili powder, salt, and pepper.  Mix with hands to coat. 2.  In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and then add chicken. Cook for 5 minutes. Flip to cook other side for additional 5 minutes or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165°F (77°C). 3.  In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, honey minced garlic, rice vinegar, chili garlic hot sauce, and minced ginger. 4.  Pour honey garlic mixture over chicken and simmer for 2 minutes before serving.

fields.name: AIR FRIED CHICKEN PARMESAN
fields.ingredients: 32 ounces chicken breast, flattened (905 g) 2 eggs 1/2 cup Italian breadcrumbs (55 g) 1/4 cup Panko breadcrumbs (15 g) 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon salt  1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 cup marinara sauce (255 g) 1 cup low-fat mozzarella (110 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a small bowl, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan, and seasonings. 2. In a separate bowl, whisk eggs. 3.  Dip chicken in eggs and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Repeat process with remaining chicken. 4.  Place chicken in a single layer of air fryer basket, and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 5.  Cook at  375°F (190°F) for 18-20 minutes or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F, flipping halfway. 6.  Remove chicken from basket and pour marinara sauce over chicken. Sprinkle mozzarella on top of sauce.

fields.name: CREAMY BUFFALO CHICKEN PASTA
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces cooked chicken breasts, sliced (455 g) 2 tablespoons light butter (30 g) 1 cup diced onions (120 g) 2 tablespoons minced garlic (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper 10 ounces pasta (285 g) 1/2 cup light sour cream (120 g) 1/2 cup plain fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 tablespoon ranch powder (10 g) 1/2 cup Buffalo hot sauce (120 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a pan, melt butter on medium heat. Add minced garlic and onion, and saute until onion is translucent. 2.  Add cooked chicken, seasonings, sour cream, Greek yogurt to pan. Continue stirring. 3.  Add ranch dressing and buffalo sauce. Mix to combine. Leave sauce simmering on low heat. 4.  Cook pasta according to package instructions. Once cooked, drain and transfer to mixing bowl. 5. Combine pasta and creamy sauce.

fields.name: CHIPOTLE STEAK QUESADILLA
fields.ingredients: MARINADE 2 chipotle peppers in adobo sauce 3 tablespoons minced garlic (45 g) 1/2 cup red onion, chopped (75 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon chili powder 1 teaspoon oregano 1 teaspoon cumin 1/2 teaspoon salt  1/2 teaspoon pepper FOR QUESADILLA 4 oz steak (115 g) 1 tortilla 1 green bell pepper, sliced (165 g) 1/2 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (55 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a food processor, combine all marinade ingredients and process until smooth. 2.  Pour processed mixture into sealable plastic bag. 3.  Season steak with salt and pepper, then add to bag with marinade. Let marinate for at least 30 minutes in refrigerator. 4.  Discard marinade, and cook steak on stove top for 3-5 minutes. 5. Slice steak into small cubes. 6.  Place tortilla in pan. Top with steak and bell pepper, distributing to one side of tortilla. Sprinkle with cheese. Fold tortilla in half to enclose fillings. 7. Cook quesadilla for 3 minutes per side. 8. Cut in quarter slices and serve.

fields.name: AIR FRIED CRISPY CHICKEN NUGGETS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground chicken (455 g) 1/4 cup breadcrumbs (30 g) 1 cup Panko breadcrumbs (60 g) 1/2 tsp onion powder 1/2 tsp garlic powder 1/2 tsp paprika 1/2 tsp chili powder 1/2 tsp salt 1/2 tsp pepper 2 eggs, beaten
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine chicken, salt, pepper and breadcrumbs. 2.  In a second bowl, combine breadcrumbs and remainder of seasonings. 3. In a third bowl, place beaten eggs. 4.  Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. 5.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 6.  Cook at 350°F (177°C) for 15 minutes, flipping halfway.

fields.name: CREAMY MAC & CHEESE
fields.ingredients: 3 cups of water (720 ml) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml) 2 tablespoons light butter (30 g) 3 tablespoons mustard (45 g) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt  1/2 teaspoon pepper 3 cups elbow pasta (670 g) 1-1/4 cup low-fat shredded cheddar cheese (140 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (120 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a pot, combine water, milk, butter, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.  Bring to a boil. 2.  Add pasta and cook for 7-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3.  Remove from heat. Stir in cheddar cheese and yogurt, mix well to combine.

fields.name: RESTAURANT-STYLE CHIPOTLE CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: MARINADE 2 chipotle pepper in adobo sauce 3 tablespoons minced garlic (45 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1/2 cup chopped red onion (75 g) 1 teaspoon chili powder  1 teaspoon oregano 1 teaspoon cumin 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper   2 lbs chicken breast (905 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine all marinade ingredients and blend until smooth. Pour into sealable plastic bag. 2.  Poke holes in chicken breasts using fork and add to bag with marinade. 3.  Marinate for at least 30 minutes in refrigerator. 4.  Spray a skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat on medium. Cook the chicken for 6-8 minutes each side or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). 5.  Transfer to a cutting board and slice into small cubes. 6.  Use this recipe to create chipotle chicken burrito bowls, burritos, or quesadillas.

fields.name: CRUNCHY HANDHELD BEEF TACO WRAP
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces ground beef (455 g) 1 tablespoon minced garlic (15 g) 1 teaspoon cumin 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon chili powder 1/2 teaspoon pepper WRAP INGREDIENTS 4 tostada shells 4 large tortillas 1/4 cup nacho cheese dip (60 g) 1/4 cup Greek yogurt (55 g) 1/4 cup shredded romaine lettuce (15 g) 1/4 tomatoes, diced (40 g) 1 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (115 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray and place over medium heat. 2.  Add beef, garlic, and seasonings. Break beef into pieces with spatula. Cook for 10 minutes or until beef reaches internal temperature of 160’F (71’C). 3. Lay tortilla on a flat surface. 4.  Top tortilla with beef. Drizzle nacho cheese on top. Place tostada shell over cheese.  5.  Spread a thin layer of Greek yogurt over tostada shell. 6. Top with lettuce, tomato, and cheese. 7.  Fold edges of tortilla over center, covering the fillings. 8. Spray tortilla with cooking spray. 9.  Place wrap seam-side down onto a preheated skillet. Cook for 1-2 minutes, flip over and cook an additional 1-2 minutes or until golden- brown.

fields.name: COOL RANCH CHICKEN TENDERS
fields.ingredients: 4 ounce cool ranch chips, crushed (115 g) 1 cup Panko breadcrumbs (60 g) 1 tablespoon ranch powder (3 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon onion powder 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon  1/2 cup flour (60 g) 2 eggs 2 lbs chicken breast tenderloins (905 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine crushed chips, breadcrumbs, ranch powder, garlic powder, onion powder, and paprika. 2. In a separate bowl, beat eggs. 3. In a third bowl, combine flour, salt, and pepper. 4.  Dip chicken in eggs, flour, then breadcrumb mixture. 5.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Cook at 350°F (177°C) for 15 minutes or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: HEALTHY PEPPERONI PIZZA
fields.ingredients: 6 small naan rounds 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 3/4 cup pizza sauce (180 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 2-1/4 cup fat free mozzarella cheese (250 g) 9 turkey pepperoni, cut into quarters (15 g) 1/2 teaspoon basil
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2. Place naan rounds in a baking dish. 3.  Brush naan rounds with olive oil. Spread sauce pizza on top. Top with seasonings, cheese, pepperoni, and basil. 4. Bake for 8 minutes.

fields.name: AIR FRIED CRISPY COCONUT SHRIMP
fields.ingredients: 12 ounces cooked shrimp (340 g) 1/4 cup flour (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon dried parsley 2 eggs  3/4 cup coconut flakes (45 g) 1/4 cup Panko breadcrumb (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine flour and seasonings. In another bowl, beat eggs. 2.  In a third bowl, combine coconut flakes and breadcrumbs. 3.  Dip shrimp in flour, then eggs, then breadcrumb mixture to coat. 4.  Place shrimp in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 5.  Cook at 350°F (177°C) for 10 minutes or until crispy.

fields.name: ORANGE CHICKEN
fields.ingredients: 2 lbs chicken breast, cubed (905 g) 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt  1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon pepper   ORANGE SAUCE 2 tablespoons sesame oil (30 ml) 2 tablespoons minced garlic (30 g) 2 tablespoons grated ginger (30 g) 1 cup orange juice (240 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 3 tablespoons soy sauce (45 ml) 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar (15 ml) 2 tablespoons cornstarch (15 g) 1 tablespoon orange zest 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Spray a baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Add chicken to baking dish and season with garlic powder, salt, paprika, and pepper. 3.  Bake for 25 minutes or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). 4.  In a skillet over medium heat, add sesame oil, garlic and ginger. 5.  Stir in orange juice, sweetener, soy sauce, vinegar, orange zest, crushed red pepper, and cornstarch. Continue stirring for 5 minutes or until thickened. 6. Add chicken to sauce and stir to coat. 7. If desired, serve with white rice.

fields.name: RESTAURANT-STYLE CRISPY CHICKEN NUGGETS
fields.ingredients: MARINADE 1 pound chicken breast, cubed (455 g) 1 cup pickle juice (240 ml) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml)   BREADING 1 cup oat flour (120 g) 1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder  1/2 teaspoon onion powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Place marinade ingredients into sealable plastic bag. Add chicken to bag with marinade. Let marinate for at least 1 hour in refrigerator. 2.  In a bowl, combine breading ingredients and mix well. 3.  Remove chicken from marinade and coat chicken in breading mixture. 4.  Place chicken in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Cook at  375°F (190°F) for 15 minutes or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C).

fields.name: PROTEIN PEANUT BUTTER CUPS
fields.ingredients: 1 cup vanilla whey protein powder (120 g) 1/3 cup peanut butter, softened (80 g) 1/3 cup almond milk (80 ml) 1 teaspoon liquid sweetener (5 ml) 1/4 cup sugar-free chocolate chips (60 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine protein powder, peanut butter, almond milk, and sweetener. 2.  In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave for 30 seconds, stir, and microwave for additional 15 seconds or until melted. 3.  Line muffin pan with 9 baking cups and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Scoop 1 tablespoon peanut butter mixture into each. 4.  Once peanut butter mixture has set, drizzle tops with chocolate mixture. 5.  Freeze for 30 minutes or until set. Store in freezer or refrigerator.

fields.name: PROTEIN PEANUT BUTTER COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup peanut butter (260 g) 2/3 cup sweetener (50 g) 1 egg, beaten 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. 3.  Cover baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray. 4.  Form dough into 12 cookies. Using a fork, press down lightly onto tops of cookies to form criss-cross marks. 5.  Bake for 10–12 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE AVOCADO PROTEIN COOKIE
fields.ingredients: 1 avocado, halved and pitted (150 g) 2 bananas, mashed (200 g) 1/2 cup oats (40 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g) 2 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Line baking sheet with parchment paper. 2.  Scrape out insides of avocado into a mixing bowl and mash using fork. 3.  Add remaining ingredients to bowl and mix together to form dough. 4.  Form dough into 7 cookies and place on prepared baking sheet. 5.  Bake for 15 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE-CHIP PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup coconut flour (70 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/4 cup chocolate chips (60 g) 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 egg 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 325°F (163°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and stir to form dough. If dough doesn’t form, add 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. Let sit in refrigerator for 10 minutes. 3.  Form dough into 8 cookies and place on baking pan. Bake for 10–12 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: LEMON POPPY SEED PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1/4 cup lemon juice (60 ml) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1 egg 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons honey (40 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon poppy seeds (10 g) 1 tablespoon lemon zest (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon xanthan gum 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 325°F (163°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and stir to form dough. If dough doesn’t form, add 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. Let sit in refrigerator for 10 minutes. 3.  Form dough into 8 cookies and place on baking pan. Bake for 10–12 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: SNICKERDOODLE PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: DOUGH 1/4 cup agave nectar (85 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1 egg 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml), plus more as         needed 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon ground flax (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1/2 teaspoon xanthan gum 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar 1/2 teaspoon salt COATING 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 2 teaspoons cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 325°F (163°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  Make the dough:  In a large mixing bowl, combine dough ingredients and stir to form dough. If dough doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. Let sit in refrigerator for 10 minutes. 3.  Form dough into 8 cookies and place on prepared pan. Bake for 10–12 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  Make the coating:  On a plate, combine sweetener and cinnamon. Press cookies into mixture.

fields.name: OATMEAL RAISIN PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup oat flour (40 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/4 cup raisins (40 g) 1 egg, beaten 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 325°F (163°C). Line a baking pan with parchment paper. 2.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and stir to form dough. If dough doesn’t form, add 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. Let sit in refrigerator for 10 minutes. 3.  Form dough into 8 cookies and place on baking pan. Bake for 10–12 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: CHEESECAKE PROTEIN BROWNIES
fields.ingredients: CHOCOLATE BROWNIE 1 cup flour (120 g) 2 eggs 1/4 cup applesauce (60 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 2 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (30 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt CHEESECAKE SWIRL 8 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (225 g)  1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine brownie ingredients and stir until smooth. 3.  In a separate mixing bowl, combine cheesecake ingredients and mix together with handheld mixer. 4.  Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour brownie batter into pan. Distribute cheesecake mixture evenly on top of brownie batter using a spoon. Cut through batter with knife to swirl together. 5.  Bake for 30–35 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. Cut into 9 brownies.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN BROWNIES
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained (425 g) 1/2 cup peanut butter, softened (130 g) 1/4 cup light chocolate syrup (65 g) 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce (60 g) 1/4 cup oats (20 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 3 eggs 2 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (60 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon baking powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with non- stick cooking spray. 2.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Pour batter into prepared pan. 3.  Bake for 25–30 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. Cut into 9 brownies.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE HAZELNUT PROTEIN BROWNIES
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can black beans, drained (425 g) 2/3 cup sweetener (50 g) 1/4 cup chocolate hazelnut spread (75 g) 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce (60 g) 1/4 cup oats (20 g) 3 eggs 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 teaspoon caramel extract 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon baking powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with non- stick cooking spray. 2.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Pour batter into prepared pan. 3.  Bake for 25–30 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. Cut into 9 brownies.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PROTEIN CAKE
fields.ingredients: 1 banana, mashed (100 g) 1 egg, beaten 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons flour (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil, melted (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon baking powder 1/4 teaspoon salt 2 tablespoons sugar-free chocolate syrup (35 g) 1 tablespoon chocolate chips (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Coat microwave-safe bowl with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, stir together banana, egg, protein powder, flour, sweetener, coconut oil, vanilla extract, baking powder, and salt. 3.  Microwave for 45 seconds and stir again. If not done, stir and continue to microwave in 15-second intervals. 4. Top with chocolate syrup and chocolate chips.

fields.name: CLASSIC PROTEIN CHEESECAKE
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (680 g) 3 eggs 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon lemon juice (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 reduced-fat 9-inch pie crust (170 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine cream cheese, eggs, protein powder, sweetener, coconut oil, lemon juice, and vanilla extract. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. 3.  Pour batter into pie crust. Bake for 40–45 minutes. 4.  Let cheesecake set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY PROTEIN CHEESECAKE
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (680 g)  3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/4 cup strawberry pie filling (70 g) 3 eggs 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon strawberry extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. 3.  Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pie plate. Bake for 40– 45 minutes. 4.  Let cheesecake set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: BLUEBERRY PROTEIN CHEESECAKE
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (680 g) 1 cup blueberries (140 g) 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 3 eggs 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, blueberries, protein powder, sweetener, eggs, and vanilla extract. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. 3.  Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pie plate. Bake for 45– 50 minutes. 4.  Let cheesecake set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN CHEESECAKE
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (680 g) 3 scoops whey protein powder (90 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/4 cup peanut butter, softened (65 g) 1/4 cup powdered peanut butter (25 g) 3 tablespoons baking cocoa (15 g) 1 teaspoon caramel extract (5 ml) 3 eggs 8 mini peanut butter cups, crumbled
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, protein powder, sweetener, peanut butter, powdered peanut butter, baking cocoa, caramel extract, and eggs. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. Stir in peanut butter cups. 3.  Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pie plate. Bake for 45– 50 minutes. 4.  Let cheesecake set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: COOKIES-AND-CREAM PROTEIN CHEESECAKE
fields.ingredients: 24 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (680 g) 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 3 eggs 10 cream-filled cookies
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, protein powder, sweetener, vanilla extract, and eggs. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. Stir in cream-filled cookies. 3.  Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pie plate. Bake for 45– 50 minutes. 4.  Let cheesecake set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: PUMPKIN PROTEIN PIE
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can pumpkin puree (425 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (120 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 3 egg whites 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice 2 teaspoons vanilla extract (10 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 reduced-fat 9-inch pie crust (170 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except pie crust. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. 3.  Pour batter into pie crust. Bake for 40–45 minutes. 4.  Let pie set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: SWEET POTATO PROTEIN PIE
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces sweet potatoes, cooked (455 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 2 eggs 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (30 g) 2 teaspoons vanilla extract (10 ml) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 reduced-fat 9-inch pie crust (170 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C). 2.  Remove skin from sweet potatoes and mash in mixing bowl. 3.  Add all other ingredients except pie crust. Mix with handheld mixer until smooth. 4.  Pour batter into pie crust. Bake for 45–50 minutes. 5.  Let pie set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Cut into 8 slices.

fields.name: BLUEBERRY PROTEIN MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup flour (90 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 egg 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 teaspoons vanilla extract (10 ml) 1 teaspoon xanthan gum (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 cup blueberries (140 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except blueberries and mix until smooth. If batter doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 3.  Add blueberries to batter and stir. 4.  Line muffin tray with 9 silicone baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups and bake for 20-25 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: LEMON POPPY-SEED PROTEIN MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup flour (90 g) 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup lemon juice (60 ml) 1 egg 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 tablespoons poppy seeds (15 g) 1 tablespoon lemon zest (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon xanthan gum (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until smooth. If batter doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 3.  Line muffin tray with 9 silicone baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups. Bake for 20–25 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY PROTEIN MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup flour (90 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1 egg 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 1 teaspoon xanthan gum (5 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon strawberry extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 cup strawberries, diced (160 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients except strawberries and mix until smooth. If batter doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 3. Add strawberries to batter and stir. 4.  Line muffin tray with 9 silicone baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups and bake for 20–25 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: GLAZED CARROT-CAKE PROTEIN MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: MUFFINS 1 cup carrots, shredded (130 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup flour (90 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (35 g) 1 egg 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 teaspoons cinnamon 2 teaspoons vanilla extract (10 ml) 1 teaspoon ground nutmeg 1 teaspoon xanthan gum 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt GLAZE 2 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (55 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all muffin ingredients and mix until batter forms. If batter doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 3.  Line muffin tray with 9 silicone baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups and bake for 20–25 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In a bowl, combine glaze ingredients and mix until smooth. Spread on top of muffins.

fields.name: GLAZED PUMPKIN PROTEIN MUFFINS
fields.ingredients: MUFFINS 1 cup pumpkin (240 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 cup flour (90 g) 1/2 cup coconut flour (70 g) 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/4 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (55 g) 1 egg 3 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (90 g) 2 teaspoons cinnamon 2 teaspoons vanilla extract (10 ml) 1 teaspoon ground nutmeg 1 teaspoon xanthan gum 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt GLAZE 2 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (55 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all muffin ingredients and mix until smooth. If batter doesn’t form, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 3.  Line muffin tray with 9 silicon baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups and bake for 20–25 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In a bowl, combine glaze ingredients and mix until smooth. Spread on top of muffins.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY PROTEIN BREAD
fields.ingredients: 2 bananas, mashed (200 g) 1 cup oat flour (80 g) 1 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (230 g) 1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce (60 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 2 egg whites 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (30 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon strawberry extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 1/2 teaspoon salt 3/4 cup strawberries, sliced (120 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, mix together all ingredients except strawberries. 3.  Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pan. 4.  Top batter with sliced strawberries. Bake for 35–40 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 5. Remove from pan and slice into 7 slices.

fields.name: GLAZED PUMPKIN PROTEIN BREAD
fields.ingredients: PUMPKIN BREAD 1 cup flour (120 g) 1 cup pumpkin (240 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/3 cup almond milk (80 ml) 1 egg 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted (30 g) 1 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger 1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg 1/2 teaspoon salt GLAZE 4 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (110 g)  3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). 2.  In a bowl, mix together all pumpkin bread ingredients. 3.  Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pan. Bake for 35–40 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 4.  In a bowl, combine glaze ingredients and mix until smooth. Spread on top of bread loaf. Remove from pan and slice into 7 slices.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY PROTEIN FLUFF
fields.ingredients: 1 3/4 cups strawberries, frozen (230 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 1/2 scoops vanilla casein protein powder (45 g) 2 tablespoons pasteurized egg whites (30 ml) 1 teaspoon xanthan gum (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine strawberries and almond milk and blend until smooth. Pour into large mixing bowl. 2.  Add remaining ingredients to bowl. Using hand mixer, blend for 10 minutes to form fluff.

fields.name: BANANA CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN FLUFF
fields.ingredients: 1 3/4 cups sliced banana, frozen (260 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 1/2 scoops vanilla casein protein powder (45 g) 2 tablespoons pasteurized egg whites (30 ml) 1 teaspoon xanthan gum (5 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate chips (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine banana and almond milk and blend until smooth. Pour into large mixing bowl. 2.  Add all ingredients except chocolate chips to bowl. Using hand mixer, blend for 10 minutes to form fluff. 3. Stir in chocolate chips.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY BANANA PROTEIN GELATIN
fields.ingredients: 1 cup boiling water (240 ml) 1 pack sugar-free strawberry gelatin mix (90 g) 1 cup cold water (240 ml) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 banana, sliced (100 g) 2 tablespoons light whipped cream (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a pot over medium to high heat, boil water and add gelatin mix. Stir until mixture dissolves and turn off stove. 2.  In a shaker bottle, combine cold water and protein powder. Shake until powder dissolves. Pour into pot and stir. 3.  Pour contents of pot into container or bowl. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Top with banana and whipped cream.

fields.name: PROTEIN COOKIE DOUGH
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can garbanzo beans, rinsed and         drained (425 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/4 cup peanut butter, softened (65 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and blend until smooth. 2.  Transfer to a bowl and add chocolate chips. Leave in freezer for 45 minutes.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN BALLS
fields.ingredients: 1 cup peanut butter, softened (255 g) 3/4 cup oats (60 g) 4 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (120 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, mix together peanut butter, oats, and protein powder. 2.  Add sweetener, almond milk, and vanilla extract and mix again. 3.  Roll mixture into 16 balls with hands and place on plate. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Store in freezer or refrigerator.

fields.name: PEANUT-BUTTER BANANA PROTEIN POPSICLES
fields.ingredients: 1 banana (100 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/4 cup peanut butter (65 g) 3 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (90 g) 3 tablespoons baking cocoa (15 g) 3 tablespoons sweetener (15 g) 1 cup almond milk (240 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. 2.  Pour batter into 6 popsicle molds. Freeze for at least 4 hours.

fields.name: PEANUT-BUTTER CHOCOLATE GRANOLA
fields.ingredients: 3 cups oats (240 g) 3 tablespoons peanut butter (50 g) 2 tablespoons baking cocoa (10 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup light syrup (60 ml) 1/4 cup chocolate chips (60 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Spray nonstick cooking spray on a baking sheet. 2.  Add oats to a mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, combine peanut butter, baking cocoa, almond milk, coconut oil, vanilla extract, protein powder, sweetener, and syrup. Stir until smooth. Add additional almond milk as needed. 3.  Pour peanut butter mixture over oats and mix. Transfer to prepared baking sheet. 4.  Lightly spray tops of oat mixture with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes, shaking halfway. Let cool on counter for 30 minutes. 5. Add chocolate chips and store.

fields.name: PROTEIN MARSHMALLOW RICE CAKES
fields.ingredients: 4 cups crisped rice cereal (105 g) 1/2 cup honey (170 g) 1/2 cup peanut butter, melted (65 g) 4 scoops whey protein powder (120 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a large mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients. Add additional almond milk as needed. 2.  Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Press mixture into pan to form even layer. Freeze for 30 minutes. 3.  Cut into 9 pieces. Store in refrigerator.

fields.name: FOUR-INGREDIENT PROTEIN BARS
fields.ingredients: 2 cups oats (160 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 5 tablespoons peanut butter (80 g) 4 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (120 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In large mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients. Add additional almond milk as needed. 2.  Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Press mixture into pan to form even layer. Freeze for 30 minutes. 3. Cut into 8 bars. Store in refrigerator.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER CRISP PROTEIN BARS
fields.ingredients: 1 1/2 cups oat flour (120 g) 1 cup crisped rice cereal (30 g) 3/4 cup peanut butter, melted (190 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/4 cup agave nectar (85 g) 4 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (120 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1.  In a large mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients. Add additional almond milk as needed. 2.  Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Press mixture into baking pan to form even layer. Freeze for 30 minutes. 3. Cut into 8 bars. Store in refrigerator.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PROTEIN PUDDING
fields.ingredients: 1 avocado, halved and pitted (150 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 2 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (60 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Scrape out insides of avocado into a bowl and mash with a fork. 2.  Add remaining ingredients to bowl and mix. Freeze for 30 minutes.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PROTEIN ICE CREAM
fields.ingredients: 3 bananas, sliced and frozen (300 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 2 scoops chocolate whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons baking cocoa (15 g) 2 tablespoons light chocolate syrup (35 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. 2.  Pour into bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Freeze for at least 5 hours. 3.  Remove from freezer and scoop serving of ice cream into separate bowl.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY BANANA PROTEIN ICE CREAM
fields.ingredients: 2 bananas, frozen (200 g) 1/4 cup strawberries, sliced (40 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon strawberry extract
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Add more almond milk as needed. 2.  Pour into bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Freeze for 15–20 minutes. 3.  Remove from freezer and scoop serving of ice cream into separate bowl.

fields.name: MINT CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN ICE CREAM
fields.ingredients: 2 bananas, frozen (200 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons almond milk (30 ml) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon peppermint extract 3 drops green food coloring 2 tablespoons chocolate chips (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and blend until smooth. Add more almond milk as needed. 2.  Pour into bowl and stir in chocolate chips. Cover with aluminum foil and place in freezer for 15–20 minutes. 3.  Remove from freezer and scoop serving of ice cream into separate bowl.

fields.name: COOKIES AND CREAM PROTEIN ICE CREAM
fields.ingredients: 2 bananas, frozen (200 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 2 cream-filled cookies, crumbled (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients except cookies and blend until smooth. Add more almond milk as needed. 2.  Pour into bowl and stir in cookies. Cover with aluminum foil and freeze for 15–20 minutes. 3.  Remove from freezer and scoop serving of ice cream into separate bowl.

fields.name: MANGO PROTEIN FROZEN YOGURT
fields.ingredients: 1 1/2 cups mango, frozen (240 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Scrape insides of blender with spoon if frozen yogurt doesn’t form. 2.  Pour into bowl and place in freezer for 15-20 minutes.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY KIWI PROTEIN FROZEN YOGURT
fields.ingredients: 1 cup strawberries, frozen (150 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup kiwi, frozen (75 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Scrape insides of blender with spoon if frozen yogurt doesn’t form. 2.  Pour into bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Freeze for 15–20 minutes.

fields.name: PINA COLADA PROTEIN FROZEN YOGURT
fields.ingredients: 1 1/2 cups pineapple, frozen (240 g) 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon coconut extract (5 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Scrape insides of blender with spoon if frozen yogurt doesn’t form. 2.  Pour into bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Freeze for 15–20 minutes.

fields.name: PROTEIN PUMPKIN PIE
fields.ingredients: 1-3/4 cup canned pumpkin (430 g) 1-1/2 cup almond milk (360 ml) 2 eggs 2 egg whites 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/2 cup brown sugar sweetener (40 g) 1/3 cup sweetener (25 g) 1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon xanthan gum
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until smooth. 3.  Coat 9-inch pie pan with non-stick cooking spray. 4.  Pour batter into pan and bake for 50-55 minutes. Allow to cool for 2 hours on counter. 5. Refrigerate for 4-6 hours or overnight.

fields.name: SNICKERDOODLE PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (30 g) 1/4 cup zero calorie sweetener (20 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon 1/2 teaspoon xanthan gum 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/4 cup light syrup (60 ml) 1 egg 2 tablespoons light melted butter (30 g) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract Sprinkle of cinnamon
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 325°F (163°C). 2.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. 3. Refrigerate dough for 10 minutes. 4.  Cover baking sheet with parchment paper. Form dough into 6 cookies and place on baking sheet and lightly press down on center of each cookie with a fork. 5.  Bake for 8-10 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes and sprinkle with cinnamon.

fields.name: COOKIES & CREAM PROTEIN COOKIE DOUGH
fields.ingredients: 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 scoop casein protein (30 g) 3 tablespoons coconut flour (20 g) 1-1/2 tablespoon sweetener (8 g) 1 tablespoon sugar-free pudding mix (10 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 2/3 cup almond milk (160 ml) 1 teaspoon light melted butter (5 g) 3 cream-filled cookies, crushed
fields.recipe: 1.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. 2. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.

fields.name: COOKIES AND CREAM PROTEIN BARS
fields.ingredients: BARS 1-1/4 cup oat flour (120 g) 4 scoops whey protein powder (120 g) 1/2 cup crushed cream-filled cookies (30 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g)    1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 cup peanut butter (130 g) 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract  TOPPING 3/4 cup Greek yogurt (170 g) 1/2 scoop whey protein powder (15 g) 1 tablespoon sugar free pudding mix (10 g) 2 teaspoons sweetener (10 g) 3 cream-filled cookies, crushed
fields.recipe: 1. In a mixing bowl, combine all bar ingredients. 2.  Line a baking dish with parchment paper. Press bar mixture into dish to form even layer. Freeze for 45 minutes. 3.  Whisk together all  topping ingredients except cream-filled cookies. 4.  Remove bars from baking dish and cover with topping. 5.  Sprinkle with crushed cream-filled cookies. 6. Cut into 8 bars.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE CHIP PROTEIN COOKIE DOUGH
fields.ingredients: 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 scoop casein protein (30 g) 2 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (15 g) 2 tablespoons coconut flour (15 g) 1 tablespoon brown sugar sweetener (5g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon salt 1-1/2 tablespoons mini chocolate chips (20 g) 1 teaspoon light melted butter (5 g) 2/3 cup almond milk (160 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. If too dry, add additional 1 tablespoon almond milk at a time and stir. 2. Freeze for 10 minutes.

fields.name: PUMPKIN PROTEIN CUPCAKES
fields.ingredients: BATTER 1 cup flour (120 g) 1/2 cup zero calorie sweetener (40 g) 2 scoops vanilla whey protein powder (60 g) 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice 1-1/2 teaspoons baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1 cup pumpkin (245 g) 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 egg 3 tablespoons light melted butter (45 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract   FROSTING 4 ounces low-fat cream cheese (115 g) 3/4 cup Greek yogurt (170 g) 1/2 cup light whipped topping (35 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1/2 cup zero calorie sweetener (40 g) 1 tablespoon vanilla sugar-free pudding mix (10 g) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all batter ingredients and mix until smooth. 3.  Line muffin tray with 12 silicone baking cups. Pour batter into baking cups and bake for 18- 20 minutes. 4. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 5.  In another bowl, combine all frosting ingredients and mix until smooth.  Top cupcakes with frosting.

fields.name: PUMPKIN PROTEIN BREAD
fields.ingredients: 2-1/4 cup pumpkin (305 g) 3 eggs 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (115 g) 2 tablespoons melted butter (30 g) 1 cup flour (120 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons sweetener (15 g) 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon baking soda 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 325°F (165°C). 2. In a bowl, mix together all ingredients. 3.  Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pan. Bake for 45-50 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER CUP PROTEIN ICE CREAM CAKES
fields.ingredients: 1-1/4 light whipped topping (180 g) 1 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (225 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons melted peanut butter (30 g) 2 tablespoons sugar-free pudding mix (20 g) 2 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (15 g) 1 teaspoon sweetener (5 g) 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (3 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Line muffin tray with 6 silicone baking cups. 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine whipped topping, Greek yogurt, whey protein, peanut butter, pudding mix, powdered peanut butter and sweetener. Stir to combine. 3.  Pour mixture into baking cups and freeze for 4 hours. 4.  In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave for 30 seconds, stir, and microwave for additional 15 seconds or until melted.  5.  Drizzle chocolate mixture over peanut butter cups. 6. Freeze for 5 minutes.

fields.name: COOKIES AND CREAM PROTEIN ICE CREAM CAKES
fields.ingredients: 1-1/4 light whipped topping (180 g) 1 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (225 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 2 tablespoons white chocolate sugar-free pud - ding mix (20 g) 4 cream-filled cookies, crumbled
fields.recipe: 1.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix to form a batter. 2.  Pour into baking cups. Freeze for at least 4 hours.

fields.name: CANDY BAR PROTEIN RICE CAKES
fields.ingredients: 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/4 cup light whipped topping (20 g) 3 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (20 g) 1 teaspoon sweetener (5 g) 3 tablespoons calorie-free caramel syrup (45 ml) 1 tablespoon almond milk (15 ml) 4 chocolate rice cakes 1/4 cup chocolate chips (60 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (3 g) 2 tablespoons peanuts, chopped (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine protein powder, whipped topping, powdered peanut butter, sweetener, caramel syrup, and almond milk. 2. Spread mixture on top of each rice cake. 3.  In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave for 30 seconds, stir, and microwave for additional 15 seconds or until melted. 4.  Drizzle chocolate mixture over rice cakes. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. 5. Freeze for 20 minutes.

fields.name: PROTEIN CHOCOLATE PUDDING
fields.ingredients: 1-1/4 cup almond milk (300 ml) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1 packet sugar-free pudding mix (40 g) 1/2 cup Greek yogurt (115 g) 2 tablespoons light whipped topping (10 g) 1 teaspoon sweetener (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth. 2. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER CUP PROTEIN RICE CAKES
fields.ingredients: 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 3 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (20 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1 tablespoons peanut butter (15 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 4 rice cakes 3 tablespoons chocolate chips (45 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (3 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine protein powder, powdered peanut butter, sweetener, peanut butter, and almond milk. 2. Spread the mixture on top of each rice cake. 3.  In another bowl, combine chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave for 30 seconds, stir, and microwave for additional 15 seconds or until melted. 4.  Drizzle chocolate mixture over rice cakes. Freeze for 20 minutes.

fields.name: DOUBLE CHOCOLATE PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1 avocado, mashed (150 g) 1 egg  1/2 cup baking cocoa (40 g) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 1 scoop casein protein (30 g) 2 tablespoons sweetener (10 g) 1/2 cup flour (60 g) 1/2 cup fat free Greek yogurt (120 g) 1/3 cup sugar-free syrup (50 ml) 1 teaspoon baking soda 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/3 cup chocolate chips (80 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. Fold in chocolate chips. 3. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 4. Form dough into 9 cookies and slightly flatten.  5. Bake for 8 minutes.

fields.name: PROTEIN CHEESECAKE BALLS
fields.ingredients: 8 ounce cream cheese (225 g) 1 cup oats (80 g) 2 tablespoons cheesecake  sugar-free pudding  mix (20 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/2 cup whipped topping (70 g) 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 2 Graham cracker sheets, crushed (30 g)
fields.recipe: 1. In a bowl, mix together all ingredients. 2.  Form mixture into 12 balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs. 3. Freeze for 30 minutes.

fields.name: PROTEIN FUDGE POPSICLES
fields.ingredients: 1 1/2 cup oat milk (360 ml) 1/4 cup Greek yogurt (60 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 2 scoops whey protein (60 g) 1/4 cup zero-calorie sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 2 tablespoons chocolate sugar-free pudding mix                 (20 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth. 2. Evenly distribute into 5 popsicle molds. 3. Freeze for 6 hours.

fields.name: BIRTHDAY PROTEIN MUG CAKES
fields.ingredients: CAKE 1/2 mashed banana (60 g) 1 egg  1/4 cup Greek yogurt (60 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 scoop whey protein powder (30 g) 3 tablespoons flour (25 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 tsp sprinkles 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt   FROSTING   ½ cup fat-free Greek yogurt (120 g) 1 tablespoon vanilla sugar free pudding mix (10 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)   TOPPINGS 2 teaspoons sprinkles (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. In a small bowl, mix together cake ingredients.. 2.  Spray inside of coffee mug with nonstick cooking spray and fill with batter.  Microwave for 1 minute. Stir and microwave in 30-second intervals until cooked. 3. Remove cake from mug and cut in half. 4.  In a separate bowl, combine frosting ingredients. 5.  Spread frosting on top of cakes and top with sprinkles.

fields.name: PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN COOKIES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup peanut butter (260 g) 4 scoops whey protein (120 g) 2 eggs 2 egg whites 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1/4 cup coconut flour (30 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix until dough forms. 3. Line baking sheet with parchment paper. 4.  Form dough into 23 balls and arrange on baking sheet. Flatten lightly using a fork. 5.  Bake for 6 minutes.  Let cool on counter for 20 minutes.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PROTEIN ICE CREAM
fields.ingredients: 2 sliced frozen bananas (220 g) 3 tablespoons fat-free Greek yogurt (45 g) 2 scoops whey protein (60 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients.  Blend until smooth. 2.  Pour into bowl and cover with aluminum foil. Freeze for at least 3 hours.

fields.name: CHOCOLATE PEANUT BUTTER PROTEIN BALLS
fields.ingredients: 1 cup oats (80 g) 3 scoops whey protein powder (90 g) 1 cup peanut butter (260 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 2 tbsp almond milk (30 ml) 1/4 cup chocolate chips 60 g) 1 teaspoon coconut oil (5 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  In a bowl, combine peanut butter, oats, and peanut butter. 2.  Add sweetener, almond milk, and vanilla extract and mix again until reaching dough consistency. Add additional 1 tablespoon of almond milk if needed. 3.  Roll mixture into 12 balls and place on baking sheet lined with parchment paper. 4.  In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips and coconut oil. Microwave for 30 seconds, stir and microwave for additional 15 seconds or until melted. 5. Drizzle chocolate mixture over oat balls. 6. Freeze for 30 minutes.

fields.name: HEALTHY PROTEIN BANANA BREAD
fields.ingredients: BANANA BREAD 1 cup Greek yogurt (225 g) 2 mashed ripe bananas (210 g) 1-1/2 cups oat flour (180 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/4 cup sugar-free applesauce (60 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 1 tablespoon sugar free syrup (15 ml) 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (5 ml) 1 egg 1 tsp cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°F). 2. In a bowl, mix together all ingredients. 3.  Spray a 9x5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into pan. 4. Top with crushed walnuts. 5.  Bake for 40-45 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. 6.  Remove from pan and slice into 7 slices.   Top with crushed walnuts or powdered sweetener.

fields.name: COOKIES & CREAM PROTEIN BROWNIES
fields.ingredients: 1 cup flour (120 g) 2 scoops whey protein powder (60 g) 1/4 cup sweetener (20 g) 1/4 cup baking cocoa (20 g) 1 teaspoon baking powder 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1/4 cup apple sauce 2 eggs 2 tablespoons butter, melted (30g) 1 tsp vanilla extract (5 ml)   TOPPING 2 cream-filled cookies, crushed
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine flour, protein powder, sweetener, baking cocoa, and baking powder. 3.  Stir in almond milk, apple sauce, eggs, butter, vanilla extract. Mix to combine. 4.  Spray a 8x8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour brownie batter into pan. Top with 2 crushed cream-filled cookies. 5.  Bake for 18-20 minutes. Let cool on counter for 20 minutes. Cut into 9 brownies.

fields.name: SWEET POTATO FRIES
fields.ingredients: 3 sweet potatoes, cut into fries (515 g) 2 tablespoons olive oil (30 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 teaspoon paprika
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix together with hands to coat all fries. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add fries. Bake for 10 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and brush sweet potato chips with remaining mixture from bowl. Bake for additional 10 minutes or until crispy.

fields.name: HONEY MUSTARD SWEET-POTATO WEDGES
fields.ingredients: 3 sweet potatoes, cut into wedges (515 g) 2 tablespoons olive oil 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 cup honey mustard (120 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except honey mustard. Mix together with hands to coat all wedges. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add wedges. Bake for 20 minutes, turning after 10 minutes to ensure wedges cook evenly. 4.  Remove from oven and brush with honey mustard. Bake for additional 5 minutes.

fields.name: SWEET POTATO CHIPS
fields.ingredients: 3 sweet potatoes, cut into 1/4-inch slices (515 g) 2 tablespoons olive oil (30 ml) 2 tablespoons light syrup (60 ml) 1 teaspoon hot sauce (5 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/4 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C). 2.  In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix together with hands to coat all chips. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add chips. Bake for 10 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and brush chips with remaining mixture from bowl. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until crispy.

fields.name: MASHED MARSHMALLOW SWEET POTATOES
fields.ingredients: 4 sweet potatoes (685 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 1/2 cup sweetener (40 g) 2 teaspoons cinnamon 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 1/4 cup light syrup (60 ml) 1 cup mini marshmallows (45 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). 2.  Wrap potatoes in aluminum foil and cook for one hour. Remove from foil and let cool on counter for 10 minutes. Leave oven on. 3.  Scoop insides of sweet potatoes out into mixing bowl and mash. 4.  Add butter, sweetener, cinnamon, almond milk, and syrup to bowl. Mix together using a handheld mixer until smooth. 5.  Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and add mashed sweet potatoes. Top with marshmallows and bake for 10 minutes.

fields.name: PARMESAN MASHED POTATOES
fields.ingredients: 32 ounces potatoes, peeled and chopped (910 g) 4 ounces fat-free cream cheese, softened (115 g)  3/4 cup Parmesan cheese (65 g) 1/4 cup light butter, melted (60 g) 1/2 cup chives, chopped (25 g) 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon pepper 1 teaspoon garlic powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Add potatoes to boiling water and boil for 10– 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain and pat dry. 2.  Add cooked potatoes to mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients. Mash potatoes until smooth and ingredients are combined.

fields.name: TWICE-BAKED POTATOES
fields.ingredients: 4 potatoes (685 g) 1/3 cup fat-free sour cream (160 g) 1/2 cup fat-free cheddar cheese (55 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 2 tablespoons light ranch dressing (30 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/4 cup almond milk (60 ml) 4 slices bacon, cooked and crumbled (40 g) 1/4 cup chopped green onion (25 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). 2.  Wrap potatoes in aluminum foil and cook for one hour. Remove from foil and let cool on counter for 10 minutes. Leave oven on. 3.  Cut tops of potatoes and scrape out insides into a mixing bowl, keeping outer shell of potato intact. 4.  Add sour cream, cheddar, butter, ranch dressing, seasonings, and almond milk to bowl and mash until smooth and ingredients are combined. 5.  Add mixture back into potato shells and top with bacon. Set on baking sheet and bake for 15–20 minutes. 6. Remove from oven and top with green onion.

fields.name: CAULIFLOWER MASHED POTATOES
fields.ingredients: 6 cups cauliflower florets (510 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (20 g) 1 tablespoon xanthan gum (10 g) 2 teaspoons garlic powder 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/4 cup fat-free buttermilk (60 ml) 1/4 cup chives, chopped (15 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Steam cauliflower over boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender. 2.  Transfer cauliflower to blender or food processor. Add remaining ingredients except chives and blend until smooth. 3. Transfer to bowl and top with chives.

fields.name: CILANTRO LIME CAULIFLOWER RICE
fields.ingredients: 6 cups cauliflower florets (510 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil (15 ml) 2 teaspoons garlic, minced (10 g) 2 tablespoons light butter, melted (30 g) 1/4 cup lime juice (60 ml) 1/4 cup cilantro, chopped (20 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Add cauliflower to blender or food processor and blend until texture resembles rice. 2.  In a pan, heat coconut oil over medium heat. Add cauliflower and cook for 10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl. 3.  Add butter, lime juice, cilantro, salt and pepper to bowl and stir until combined.

fields.name: ROASTED PARMESAN CAULIFLOWER
fields.ingredients: 4 cups cauliflower florets (340 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 ml) 2 teaspoons garlic powder 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese (40 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C). 2.  Add cauliflower, coconut oil, and seasonings to plastic bag and seal. Shake bag to ensure that cauliflower is coated. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add cauliflower. Bake for 30 minutes, flipping halfway. 4.  Remove from oven and sprinkle Parmesan on cauliflower. Bake for additional 10 minutes.

fields.name: BACON-WRAPPED ASPARAGUS
fields.ingredients: 21 asparagus spears, trimmed (315 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 7 slices bacon (70 g) 3 tablespoons light butter, melted (45 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 2 tablespoons soy sauce (30 ml) 1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar (10 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/4 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). 2.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add asparagus. Brush asparagus with olive oil. 3.  Take 3 pieces of asparagus and wrap from top to bottom with 1 slice of bacon. Repeat process for remaining asparagus and bacon. 4.  In a small bowl, combine butter, sweetener, soy sauce, balsamic vinegar, and seasonings. Stir until combined. Pour over asparagus and bacon. 5.  Bake for 25–30 minutes or until asparagus is tender and bacon is crispy.

fields.name: ROASTED GARLIC GREEN BEANS
fields.ingredients: 16 ounces green beans, trimmed (455 g) 2 tablespoons lemon juice (30 ml) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 2 teaspoons garlic powder 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C). 2.  In a plastic bag, combine all ingredients and seal. Shake bag to ensure that green beans are coated. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add green beans. Bake for 10 minutes, flipping halfway.

fields.name: ROASTED SESAME GINGER BROCCOLI
fields.ingredients: 4 cups broccoli florets (340 g) 3 tablespoons soy sauce (45 ml) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon sesame oil (5 ml) 1 teaspoon ground ginger 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 tablespoon sesame seeds (10 g)
fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C). 2.  In a plastic bag, combine all ingredients except sesame seeds and seal. Shake bag to ensure that broccoli is coated. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add broccoli. Bake for 10 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven, flip broccoli, sprinkle sesame seeds on broccoli, and cook for additional 5 minutes.

fields.name: BAKED MOZZARELLA TOMATO SLICES
fields.ingredients: 4 tomatoes, halved (565 g) 2 tablespoons olive oil (30 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1 cup fat-free mozzarella cheese (115 g) 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese (40 g) 2 tablespoons oregano, chopped (5 g)
