fields.recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 450°F (232°C). 2.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add tomato halves. 3.  Drizzle olive oil, salt, and pepper over tomatoes and top with mozzarella, Parmesan, and oregano. Bake for 15 minutes.

fields.name: CRISPY AVOCADO SLICES
fields.ingredients: 1 egg, beaten 1 egg white 1 1/2 cups panko breadcrumbs (90 g) 2 tablespoons Parmesan (10 g) 1 teaspoon onion powder 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon paprika 3 avocados, pitted and sliced, skin removed (450 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 450°F (232°C). Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, combine egg and egg white. In another bowl, combine panko breadcrumbs, Parmesan, and seasonings. 3.  Dip avocado slices in egg mixture and then in breadcrumb mixture to coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Sprinkle remaining breadcrumbs over avocado slices and lightly spray with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes.

fields.name: SLOW-COOKED BAKED BARBECUE BEANS
fields.ingredients: 3 (15-ounce) cans pinto beans (1,275 g) 1 cup sugar-free ketchup (240 g) 1 cup chopped onion (160 g) 3/4 cup sweetener (60 g) 1/2 cup barbecue sauce (135 g) 1 tablespoon coconut oil, melted (15 g) 2 teaspoons salt 1 teaspoon ground mustard 1 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon paprika
fields.recipe: 1.  Spray inside of slow-cooker with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Add all ingredients and stir. Cook for 4 hours on high or 6 hours on low.

fields.name: BAKED TORTILLA CHIPS
fields.ingredients: 2 tablespoons lime juice (30 ml) 1 tablespoon light butter, melted (15 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 5 tortillas, each cut into 8 equal parts 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon chili powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  In a bowl, stir together lime juice, butter, and olive oil. 3.  Place tortilla pieces on baking sheet. Brush both sides with lime juice mixture. Sprinkle with seasonings. Bake for 5 minutes. 4.  Remove from oven and flip chips to cook other side. Bake for additional 5 minutes or until crispy.

fields.name: CRISPY ROASTED CHICKPEAS
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can chickpeas, drained and rinsed (425 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 teaspoon lemon juice (5 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon chili powder 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). 2.  In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands to coat chickpeas. 3.  Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray and add chickpeas. Bake for 20–25 minutes, shaking baking sheet halfway.

fields.name: BAKED ONION RINGS
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup flour (60 g) 1 egg, beaten 1 egg white 1 cup panko breadcrumbs (60 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon onion powder 1/2 teaspoon pepper 2 onions, peeled and sliced to rings (455 g)
fields.recipe: 1.  Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. 2.  Add flour to one bowl, egg and egg white to another, and panko breadcrumbs with seasonings to a third. Mix breadcrumb bowl with hands. 3.  Dip onion rings in flour, egg whites, and then panko breadcrumbs to coat. Place on prepared baking sheet. 4.  Lightly spray tops of onion rings with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes, flipping halfway.

fields.name: GUACAMOLE
fields.ingredients: 3 avocados, halved and pitted (450 g) 1 (10-ounce) can diced tomatoes and green chilies,  drained (285 g) 1/2 cup chopped onion (80 g) 2 tablespoons lime juice (30 ml) 2 tablespoons cilantro, chopped (10 g) 1 teaspoon garlic, minced (5 g) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper
fields.recipe: 1.  Scrape out insides of avocado into bowl and mash using a fork. 2.  Add remaining ingredients and stir until combined.

fields.name: SPINACH DIP
fields.ingredients: 3 cups spinach, chopped (90 g) 1 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (230 g) 1/4 cup minced red bell pepper (45 g) 1/4 cup chopped green onion (25 g) 2 tablespoons light mayonnaise (30 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (30 ml) 1 tablespoon lemon juice (15 ml) 1 teaspoon garlic powder 1 teaspoon dill 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon onion powder
fields.recipe: 1.  Add all ingredients to bowl and stir until combined.

fields.name: HUMMUS
fields.ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can chickpeas, drained and rinsed (425 g)  1 tablespoon tahini (15 g) 1 tablespoon olive oil (15 ml) 1 tablespoon water (15 ml) 1 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon paprika 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin 1/4 cup lemon juice (60 ml)
fields.recipe: 1.  Add all ingredients to blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. 2. Transfer to bowl and serve.

fields.name: CRISPY MOZZARELLA STICKS
fields.ingredients: 8 mozzarella sticks, halved 2 eggs 1/2 cup flour 1/2 cup panko bread crumbs 1/2 cup Italian bread crumbs 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon oregano 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
fields.recipe: 1. In a bowl, whisk eggs. 2.  In a second bowl, combine breadcrumbs and seasonings. 3. In a third bowl, add flour. 4.  Dredge mozzarella sticks into beaten eggs, flour, additional egg mixture, then bread crumbs. Repeat the process with remaining mozzarella sticks. 5.  Spray with nonstick cooking spray and place in freezer for 45 minutes. 6.  Place mozzarella sticks in a single layer in air fryer basket and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Cook at 400°F (205°C) for 6-8 minutes.

fields.name: BIRTHDAY CAKE PROTEIN SHAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup low-fat cottage cheese (115 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon vanilla sugar-free gelatin mix (5 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 cup ice cubes 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract 1 teaspoon sprinkles
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients except sprinkles. Blend until smooth. 2. Top with sprinkles.

fields.name: APPLE-PIE PROTEIN SHAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup low-fat cottage cheese (115 g) 1/2 apple, sliced (80 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sugar-free butterscotch gelatin mix (10 g)  1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon 1 cup ice cubes 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth.

fields.name: PIÑA COLADA PROTEIN SHAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup chopped pineapple, frozen (80 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 cup ice cubes 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 teaspoon coconut extract 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth.

fields.name: PEANUT-BUTTER BANANA PROTEIN SHAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1 banana (100 g) 1 scoop chocolate whey protein powder (30 g) 2 tablespoons powdered peanut butter (10 g) 1 tablespoon peanut butter (15 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 cup ice cubes 1/2 cup almond milk (120 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
fields.recipe: 1.  In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth.

fields.name: STRAWBERRY BANANA PROTEIN SHAKE
fields.ingredients: 1/2 cup fat-free Greek yogurt (115 g) 1/2 cup strawberries, frozen (80 g) 1/2 banana (50 g) 1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder (30 g) 1 tablespoon sweetener (5 g) 1 cup ice cubes 3/4 cup almond milk (180 ml) 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
